\id ACT - - Preaching things of men who has Yesu's authory- Nama Back Translation
\c 1
\s Yesu taken up heaven
\p
\v 1 In my first book, Tiofilus, I wrote you about all [the things] what Yesu began to do and to teach \v 2 and he gave his teaching thing through the God Spirit to the men with his authority whom he had chosen, and then the day became when he was taken up/note: he(God) took him(Yesu) up/ to heaven. \v 3 After his suffering, he started showing himself to these people and he started saying true talk that I am alive. When he appeared to them clearly [during] next 40 days and spoke about the ruling of God. \v 4 In one day, when they was eating with him, he said, "Don't leave Jerusalem, but wait for this goodness(gift) what my Father had told without.lying talk, [which] you.p have heard what I spoke. \v 5 Jon baptized in the water, but after a few days you will be baptized by God Spirit."
\p
\v 6 So when they met with Yesu, they asked him, "Lord, are you able to built again country of Israil in that day?"
\p
\v 7 He said to them, "These are not for you.p to know the days and times, but only God knows. \v 8 But you.p will receive the power when the God Spirit comes to you.p; and you.p will be my watching people with eyes in Jerusalem, in all of Judia and Samaria, and to the ends of the earth."
\p
\v 9 After this when he said this talk, he left them in all their eyes, and a cloud hid him from their eyes.
\p
\v 10 They were still looking up to the sky when he was going, suddenly two men with white clothes stood beside them. \v 11 They.d said, "Men from Galili region, why are you standing here looking up to the heaven? This Yesu himself whom [God] took from you into sky, will come back in this same way you.p have seen him to go to heaven.
\s They chose Matias
\p
\v 12 Then they went back to Jerusalem from mountain of Olif without-far from Jerusalem. \v 13 When they arrived, they went up to the room into the house where they were staying. There they were Fitè, Jon, Jems and Endru, Filif and Tomas, Batolome and Metyu, Jems son of Alfas and Saimon who wanted that Ju will look after/rule by themselves not by Rom's power, and Judas son of Jems. \v 14 They all continued together in talking with God with all the women and Meri the mother of Yesu and his younger brothers.
\p
\v 15 In that day Fitè stood among 120 the approving truth people \v 16 and said, "Friends, the Scripture must be happened which God Spirit spoke before from Deifid's lips what he said about Judas, who became the guide for those who held Yesu, \v 17 Judas was one of ours and saying talk man(preacher)."
\p
\v 18 Judas received money for the evil work, he bought a field, there he hung himself his body and burst widely and his intestines went out. \v 19 Everyone in Jerusalem heard about this, so they called this place in their language Akeldama, its meaning is, Place of Blood.
\p
\v 20 Fitè said, "It is already written in the Book of Sams,
\q1 'May his place be only clear,
\q2 no one who will live his place,'
\p
and
\q1 May other man take his leading place."
\p
\v 21 Therefore someone will be picked who had been with us all the days when we were moving with the Lord Yesu, \v 22 from this day when Jon baptized Yesu until he went from us. One must become a watching man with us about Yesu's rising."
\p
\v 23 So they chose two men, Matias and Josef Barsabas who was called Jèstas. \v 24 Then they talked with God, "Lord, you.s know all people's heart. Show us [one] from these two who you have chosen \v 25 to take over work of the people with Yesu's authority(apostlic work), which Judas left and went to the place he took the pain. \v 26 Then they began to play sticks to see whom God chose, and the stick fell to Matias, so he joined to the other 11 men with Yesu's authority(apostles).
\c 2
\s God Spirit came at Fentikost day
\p
\v 1 When the day of Fentakost was, they gathered together in one place. \v 2 Suddenly a sound came like the big wind from heaven and filled the whole house where they were staying. \v 3 Then they saw what looked like tongues of fire(fire flames) which spread out and sat to each person there. \v 4 All people were full of the God Spirit and the God Spirit cause/made to began to speak differently.
\p
\v 5 There were staying in Jerusalem God-fearing Ju people from different nations in the world. \v 6 When they heard this sound, a people group(crowd) came together with confusion, because one and one heard them speaking in their own talk(languages). \v 7 With very amazed, they said, "These people who was talking are like from Galili region people. \v 8 How can we hear our own language from them? \v 9 We came from Farsi, Mede, Elam, Mesofotamia, Judia, Kafadokia, Fontos, Esia, \v 10 Frigia, Famfilia, Ijif, Libia near Sailen, visitors from Rom, \v 11 Ju people and worshippers from various nations, Kreta and Arab, we hear them speaking with our own language, about this big things what God had done. \v 12 With amaze and confuse, they asked one another, "What is meaning?"
\p
\v 13 But some men made fun of them and said, "They drank new alcohol."
\s Fitè preached to the crowd
\p
\v 14 Then Fitè stood up with 11 following men, raised his voice and told to the crowd, "You men of Judia and all who stay in Jerusalem, I will explain these things to you, listen carefully what I say. \v 15 These people are not drunk, as you might think. Now is only 9 O'clock morning! \v 16 Instead, what has happened to us is what God's man who make know(prophet) Joel said,
\q1 \v 17 God says. 'Now in the last days,
\q2 I will pour my Spirit to all people,
\q2 and your sons and daughters will tell God's talk,
\q2 and your young men see eye passover things,
\q2 your old men will have dreams.
\q1 \v 18 But to my without.payment working people, men and women,
\q2 I will pour my Spirit in those days, they will tell God's talk.
\q1 \v 19 I will show special workings(miracles) in the heaven
\q2 surprising things on the earth below,
\q2 blood, fire and thick smoke.
\q1 \v 20 The sun will turn to darkness
\q2 and the moon will turn to blood
\q2 after this Lord's day comes with big and strong light(glory).
\q1 \v 21 And every people who ask on the name of the Lord, they will be saved.'
\p
\v 22 "Men of Israil, listen about this, Yesu from Najaret was a man who God proved to you by special workings(miracles), surprising things, and surprising things, which God did to you.p through him as you yourselves know. \v 23 God he knew what happen, and his first mind accepted(decided) when you.p began to beat Yesu, and you.p put him to death by nailing on the cross by Side people. \v 24 But God raised him from the death, releasing him from the pain of death, because death could not keep him. \v 25 Deifid said about him,
\q1 "'I saw the Lord always before me.
\q2 Because he is near me,
\q2 I will not be shaken.
\q1 \v 26 Then my heart is glad and my tongue rejoices,
\q2 my body in the same way will rest in hope,
\q1 \v 27 because you will not leave me with dead people,
\q2 or allow your without.dust(holy) man to rot in grave house.
\q1 \v 28 You had made known to me the paths of life,
\q2 you will fill me with joy in front of you.'
\p
\v 29 "Friends, I can tell you truly that ancester Deifid died and buried(Note: they buried him) and his grave house is here in this day. \v 30 But he was a God́’s man who make know God(prophet)and knew what God said that his descendant will be sit on his ruling sitting place. \v 31 Deifid saw next area(future) and said rising of Keriso, he said that God will not leave him into the death or he will not allowed his body rotten in the grave house. \v 32 God has raised Yesu to life, and we are really watching men by truth. \v 33 He has risen up to the right hand of God, like as what God had said, he has received God Spirit from the Father and has poured out what you.p now see and hear. \v 34 For Deifid did not send to heaven, but he himself said,
\q1 The Lord said to my Lord,
\q2 "Sit at my right hand
\q1 \v 35 until I will make your enemies
\q2 under your feet."
\p
\v 36 "So let all Israil know that you nailed this Yesu on the cross, but God had approved him Lord and Keriso."
\p
\v 37 When people heard Fitè said this, that time they fell down in the heart and said to Fitè and the other men with Yesu's authority(apostles), "Friends, what shall we do?"
\p
\v 38 Fitè answered them, "Turn away(Repent) to be baptized, all of you, in the name of Yesu Keriso in order to throw without.mind(not keep in mind and throw away)your sins away. And God will give you the God Spirit. \v 39 These without-lying talk(promises) are for you.p and your children and for all who are far away, also all whom Lord our God will call to himself."
\p
\v 40 Fitè warned them with many talks, and he said, "You.p save from this wicked generation." \v 41 Those who accepted his preaching talk began to be baptized, and that time 3,000 people were added ontop in that day.
\s The meeting of believers
\p
\v 42 They spent other time for learning from men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and for meeting together, for breaking bread and for talking with God. \v 43 Everyone was full of scaredness and saw many surprising things and surprising things by the men with Yesu's authority(apostles). \v 44 All the approving truth people gathered together and shared their things. \v 45 They were exchanging(sold) their working place and liking things(possessions), they gave to anyone who are needed. \v 46 In every day they continually met together in the worshipping house courts. They broke bread in their houses and ate together with joy and good hearts, \v 47 all the people were singing song to God and enjoying good. And the Lord added other people ontop evey day those whom he[God] saved.
\c 3
\s Fitè healed a lame beggar
\p
\v 1 One day Fitè and Jon went up to the worshipping house for talking with God at three o'clock in the afternoon. \v 2 A man was with a lame from birth they carried him to the worshipping house gate called Really good, where he sat on every day for begging to those who were going to the worshipping house. \v 3 When he saw Fitè and Jon were about to enter worshipping house, he asked them(two) for money. \v 4 Fitè looked at him straightly, also Jon. Then Fitè said, "Look at us!" \v 5 So this man gave them his respection/attention, as he thought they.dual will give something.
\p
\v 6 Then Fitè said to him, "There are not have silver and gold in me, but what is mine, I will give you. In his name Yesu Keriso from Najaret, stand and start to walk!" \v 7 Fitè took him by the right hand, he helped him to stand, at once man's feet and ankles became.d strong. \v 8 He jumped to his feet and began to walk. Then he went with them to the worshipping house, walking and jumping and praising God. \v 9 When all the people saw him in walking and in singing God, \v 10 they recognized this man who always sat begging at the worshipping house' gate called Really good, and they came wonder and amazing things with surprise what had happend to him.
\s Fitè spoke at the place of worshipping house
\p
\v 11 While the beggar held on to Fitè and Jon, all the people were surprised, came ran to them this place name Solomon's house place. \v 12 When Fitè saw this, he said to them, "Israil people, why are you surprised at this thing? Why do you look straightly at us like as by our own power or worshipping God way(godliness) we caused/made this man walk? \v 13 Ebraam's God, Aisek's God, Jeikof's God, our father's God, has glorified his worker Yesu. You.p gave him for killing and you.p rejected in front of Failet, before he had decided to let him go. \v 14 You.p rejected the Without.dust and Straight One and asked that they accepted murderer to you. \v 15 You.p killed the originator of the life, but God raised him from death. We are watching men about this. \v 16 By big mind(faith) by the name of Yesu, this man who you.p see and know, he became with strength. This is by Yesu's name and the big mind(faith) which comes through him has given him truly healing for him, which all of you see.
\p
\v 17 Friends, I know that your doing things are in the darkness of thinking(ignorance), as your head men were. \v 18 But this is how God approved what he said through his God's people who make know(prophets), saying that his Keriso will see a pain. \v 19 Turn away from sin and turn to God, so that he may take away your.p sin, so that blessing come from God, \v 20 times of supporting you from Lord and God will send Yesu, who has appointed for you.p, Yesu. \v 21 Yesu is waiting in heaven until this day comes for God in order that God will restore everything, what without-lying talk(promise) said long ago through his without.dust(holy) God's people who make know(prophets). \v 22 Moses said, "The Lord your God will raise up a God's man who make know(prophet) like as I am among your.p people, you.p must listen to what he tells you. \v 23 Whom do not listen to that man who make know(prophet) God will destroy/remove them from their people.
\p
\v 24 Since Samueluntil now, all the God's people who make know(prophets) spoke about what is happening today. \v 25 And you are sons of the God's people who make know(prophets) and you involved in what[agreement] God agree mind your ancestors. He said to Ebraam, 'In your.s offspring all peoples on earth will be in blessing.' \v 26 When God raised up his without.payment working man(servant), he sent him first to you.p to Ju people for blessing [you] in order to turn from your.p sin.
\c 4
\s Fitè and Jon stand before Ju people Ju head men's meeting
\p
\v 1 The men who sacrifice and headmen of the worshipping house guard and the Saduki men came to Fitè and Jon while they.dual were talking to the people. \v 2 They were angry because the men with Yesu's authority(apostles)(men with authority of Yesu) were reporting/preaching to the people how people will rise from dead in Yesu. \v 3 They held Fitè and Jon. They put them in darkness house. They should wait until tomorrow, because it was evening. \v 4 But many people who heard talk truly approved(believed), and in this day beliving men became 5,000 people.
\p
\v 5 The next day, leading people, head people and teaching men of the law met in Jerusalem. \v 6 Anas the leading burning sacrifice man were there, and were Kayafas, Jon, Aleksendè and the other people of the leading burning sacrifice man's family. \v 7 They brought Fitè and Jon before them and began to ask them, "By what power or by what name did you.dual do this work?"
\p
\v 8 Then Fitè, filled with the God Spirit, said to them, "Rulers and head people of the peopleǃ \v 9 If you ask me about good work for the lame who became good and how he became good, \v 10 you should know, and all the people of Israil. This is by the name of Yesu Keriso from Najaret, whom you nailed but [whom] God raised him again from the dead, this man stands before you well(healed). \v 11 Yesu is the stone you.p house builders rejected, which has become the middle post.' \v 12 Salvation will not be found to anyone, because there is no other name in the world given to people by which he will save us."
\p
\v 13 When they saw Fitè and Jon said without-fear and knew that they are without schooling or ordinary men, they were amazed and they knew that these men was with Yesu. \v 14 But because they saw a lame who had become good standing with them, then they had nothing to say. \v 15 So Ju head men sent them.d to outside from the Ju head men meeting (Sanedrin), they gathered and discussed together.
\p
\v 16 They asked, "What will we do to this two men? Everyone living in Jerusalem they know that what they.d did a surprising thing(miracle) which we cannot deny it. \v 17 But for stopping this thing keep on making know wide among the people, so that we let/make these men.dual know not to speak anymore in this name to any people."
\p
\v 18 Then they called these two men again and said strong talk(commended) them not to speak or teach by the name of Yesu. \v 19 But Fitè and Jon answered them, "You think well/carefully that is straight in God's eyes to listen(obey) to people or God. \v 20 We cannot stop talk the reason/basis of what we had seen and heard."
\p
\v 21 After stopping talk, they let them go. They could not find any way how to put guilty(to punish) them, because all the people were praising God for what had happened. \v 22 The man who became good was forty years old.
\s The believers' talking with God
\p
\v 23 When they released them.d, Fitè and Jon went to their people and told everything what the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and the head people had said to them. \v 24 When they heard this, so they raised voices together in talking with God, they said, "Lord of Lords, you made the heaven, the earth and the sea, and everything in these. \v 25 You said by God Spirit to your worker, our father Deifid,
\q1 "Why do the nations angry
\q2 and why do the peoples think without.meaning thought?
\q1 \v 26 The ruling men(kings) of the earth prepared for battle
\q2 and head men gathered together
\q1 for fighting [against] the Lord
\q2 and also with him Keriso.'"
\p
\v 27 The believers were still talk with God(pray), "Erod and Fontius Failet met together with the Side people and the people of Israil in this city in order to kill your without.dust(holy) worker Yesu, whom you have made Keriso. \v 28 They did everything, you knew with your power and in your will it would happend later. \v 29 Lord, hear and see their angers and allow your without.payment working man(servant) to speak your talk without-fearing. \v 30 Work your hand to heal and perform surprising things and surprising things through Yesu's name, your without.dust(holy) worker."
\p
\v 31 After they talked with God, that place where they were meeting was shaken. So the God Spirit filled them and they spoke the talk of God without.fear.
\s The approving truth people were distributing their own things(possessoins)
\p
\v 32 All the approving truth people were one in heart and mind. No one said that their possessions were their own, but they were distributing what were theirs. \v 33 With big power the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) kept on tell to the rising of the Lord Yesu, God's grace was rained on all the people. \v 34 There was no one was in need materials among them. Who owned land and houses were exchanging(selling) [for money]and brought them exchanged money \v 35 and put it at the men with Yesu's authority(apostles)' feet, and it was gave to anyone who had need money.
\p
\v 36 Josef, belong to a Lefi tribe from Saifres, who men with Yesu's authority(apostles) called Banabas, his name's meaning is "Son of Encouragement,'" \v 37 gave his field for [making] the money and put it to the men with Yesu's authority(apostles)' feet.
\c 5
\s Ananias and Safaira
\p
\v 1 A man name Ananias, with his wife Safaira, they sold land for money. \v 2 He kept some for himself, and his wife knew all about it, but he brought only some and put it at the men with Yesu's authority(apostles)' feet.
\p
\v 3 Then Fitè said, "Ananias, how has Sáifèr filled your heart so that you deceived the God Spirit and held for yourself some of money from which you took for the land? \v 4 Land was yours before you exchanged/sold it for money. After land selling, that money became yours. Why did you cause this way? You did not lie to people but to God."
\p
\v 5 When Ananias heard this talk, he immediately fell down and died. And big fear held all who heard what had happened. \v 6 Then young men came and wrapped his body, and carried it and they made land(buried).
\p
\v 7 Three hours later his wife came, she didn't know what happened. \v 8 Fitè asked woman, "Tell me, is this payment you and Ananias received for the land?
\p
Woman said, "Yes, that is the payment."
\p
\v 9 Fitè said to woman, "Why did you.think this mind to put Lord's Spirit for trial? Listen! That young men who buried your husband there stand in the door of house, and they will also carry you." \v 10 At once woman fell down at his feet and died. Then those young men entered in and found deadbody, carried her and buried her with her husband. \v 11 Big fear held all Yesu's family(church) and all who heard about what happened.
\s The men with Yesu's authority made good(healed) many people
\p
\v 12 The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) did many surprising things and surprising things before the people. And all the approving truth people met regularly in the Solomon's house place. \v 13 They were afraid to join them, but people spoke good talk about them. \v 14 Many men and women truly approved(believed) in the Lord and so large group became. \v 15 Therefore, people brought the sick people into the streets and put them with the stretcher and with mats so that Fitè's shadow might fall on to those people when Fitè passed by the road \v 16 Then people group also gathered from the Jerusalem city, brought their sick people and whom evil spirits spoiled and all became good.
\s They were giving suffering to the men with Yesu's authority(apostles)
\p
\v 17 Then the high burning sacrifice man(high priest) and some his helping people from Saduki group became jealous people. \v 18 They held the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and put them into the public darkness house. \v 19 But during that night a man carrying heavenly message of the Lord opened the doors of the darkness house and took them out. \v 20 He said to them, "Go, stand in the worshipping house courts, and tell the people all about this new life's talk."
\p
\v 21 When morning started(At daybreak) they entered into the worshipping house, how a man carrying heavenly message(angel) had told them, and began to teach the people.
\p
The leading burning sacrifice man and his group gathered together Sanedrin which is all the head men of Israil, then they sends guards to the darkness house to bring the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) to them. \v 22 But when they arrived at the darkness house, they did not see them. So they went back and told, \v 23 "We saw the door of the darkness house locked, with the guards standing outside, but when we opened them, we couldn't see anyone inside." \v 24 When the headman of the worshipping house guard and leading burning sacrifice men heard telling talk, they wondered what had happened to the men with Yesu's authority(apostles).
\p
\v 25 A man came said, "Listen! These men who you put in darkness house are standing in the worshipping house courts teaching the people." \v 26 Woshipping house guarders' headman went with his workers [and] brought the men with Yesu's authority(apostles). They brought them without force because they were afraid the people might stone them.
\p
\v 27 When they brought men with Yesu's authority(apostles), they made them stand before the Ju people's head men's meeting so that the leading burning sacrifice man will asked them. \v 28 He said, "We gave you.p hard talk(orders) not to teach in this name, but you.p have filled with your teaching in Jerusalem and you make us this reason/resposibity about Yesu's death."
\p
\v 29 Fitè and other men with Yesu's authority(apostles) answered, "We must obey to do to God not to people! \v 30 The God of our ancestors raised Yesu from the dead-whom you.p killed him by hanging on the cross. \v 31 God lift him up to his right hand as the ruling man(king) and saving man so that he did this so that Israil people might turn away of their sin and God will forget them. \v 32 We are watching men about these things, and God Spirit also whom God gave to those who obey to hear him.
\p
\v 33 When they heard this talk, they became with anger and wanted to put them to death. \v 34 But a Farasi man name was Gamaliel, law teaching man, who was respected by every people, he stood up in the Ju people's head people's meeting and gave talk these men be sent outside in order that they will talk in only themselves. \v 35 Then he stood to say them, "Men of Israil, think carefully what you begin to do these men. \v 36 One day, there was a man name Tèudas, who deceived that he might be big [head man], 400 people joined him. But he was killed/Note: they killed him/, all his following people were scattered and his movement finished. \v 37 After him, Judas from Galili region appeared in the days of writing name(census), [and] led the crowd with anger(revolt). He was also killed, and all his followers were scattered. \v 38 In this/these reason(s) I'm advising you.p. Leave these men! Let them go! Don't do anything! If their thought or action is from people, it will finish. \v 39 But if it comes from God, you can't stop these men, you will find yourselves [to be] enemies with God.
\p
\v 40 They took his talk. They called the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) to enter inside and began to whip. Then they said to them not to say in the name of Yesu, and they allowed and they go.
\p
\v 41 The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) left the Ju head people's meeting(Sanedrin) with joy because the name of Yesu was the reason for their suffering. \v 42 Every day in the worshipping house courts and house to house, they didn't stop teaching and preaching good talk about Yesu Keriso.
\c 6
\s Chose seven men
\p
\v 1 In those days when the approving truth people became many quickly, Grik speaking included them people began to complain to the Ibru speaking people. They were saying, "When you.p Ibru speaking people distribute food to widows every day, you are not giving enough food to Grik speaking widows." \v 2 So the 12 gathered together all approving truth people and said, "It is not straight for us to neglect the ministry of the talk of God in order to share the food. \v 3 Friends, choose 7 men from among you who are known to be full of the God Spirit and wisdom. We will give this work to them. \v 4 We ourselves will give our full time in talking with God and in preaching."
\p
\v 5 Everyone pleased this talk saying. They chose Stifèn, this man full of big mind(faith) and the God Spirit, also Filif, Frokorus, Nikanor, Timon, Farmanas, Nikolas from Antiok region who was outside man become worshipper with Ju people. \v 6 They gave these men to the men with Yesu's authority(apostles)' hand, who talked with God and laid hands on them.
\p
\v 7 So the talk of God became wide. Believers in Jerusalem became many quickly, and also many burning sacrifice men(priests) obeyed to the big mind(faith).
\s They held Stifèn
\p
\v 8 Stifèn, this man full of God's grace and power, he did big special workings(miracles) and surprising things among the people. \v 9 But some Ju people from Sairene and Aleksandria, Silisia and Esia people who called that we are Free men. These men started arguing with Stifèn, \v 10 but they could not argue with[against] him because Stifèn was with wisdom and spoke in the God Spirit's authority.
\p
\v 11 They secretly chose some men to say that, "We have heard Stifèn said wicked talk against Moses and God."
\p
\v 12 So in this way they directed people, the head people, and the teaching men of the law. They held Stifèn and brought before the Ju people' head men's meeting. \v 13 They produced lying talk, who told, "This man didn't stop talking denying talk for this worshipping house courts and against the law. \v 14 We already heard him say that this Yesu of Najaret will destroy this place and will change ancester's law which Moses have handed over to us."
\p
\v 15 All who were sitting in the Ju people's head men meeting they looked Stifen [that] his face became like of a man carrying heavenly message.
\c 7
\s Stifèn's talk to the head man's Ju head men's meeting(Sanedrin)
\p
\v 1 Then the leading burning sacrifice man asked Stifèn, "Are these complaints true?"
\p
\v 2 To this question he answered, "Friends and fathers, listen to me! With strong light(glory) our God appeared to our ancestor Ebraam when he lived in Mesofotamia, before he lived in Aran. \v 3 God said to him, 'Leave your land and your people, and go to the land which I will show you.'
\p
\v 4 So he left Kaldia people's land and stayed Aran. After his father died, God sent him to this land where you.p are now living. \v 5 God did not give any land here. But God said true talk him, 'To you and your descendants after you [God] will give the land.' At that time Ebraam had without-child. \v 6 God spoke to him in this way, 'Your.p descendants will be foreigner in other people's land, not in your.p land, they will be people's workers and they will mistreat you.p 400 years. \v 7 But I will put the pain that country that they were workers, and afterward they will come out of that country and will worship me in this place.' \v 8 God caused/made Ebraam to cut skin. Ebraam became Aisek's father and he cut skin(circumcised) him on the 8 day after his birth. Later Aisek became Jeikof's father, and Jeikof became their father of 12 sons.
\p
\v 9 Jeikof's sons started being jealous of their yonger brother Josef, they gave/sold him to Ijif as without.payment working man (slave). But He was with God \v 10 and God helped him from all his troubles. Farawa, the ruling man(king) of Ijif liked Josef because God gave him wisdom, in this reason Farawa ordered him to rule Ijif and all his household(palace).
\p
\v 11 Then a famine came in Ijif and Kanan area, famine brought big lack of food and our ancestors became without-food. \v 12 When Jeikof heard that there were rice in Ijif, he sent his sons who became our ancestors on first visit. \v 13 Their second time, Josef said his big brothers who he was, and Farawa learned about Josef's family. \v 14 After this, Josef sent them to his father Jeikof and his all family, 75 in all. \v 15 So Jeikof went to Ijif, where Jeikof and our ancestors died. \v 16 They brought back their bodies to Sekem and placed them in the grave which Ebraam took/bought from Amor's son at Sekem with money.
\p
\v 17 The day became near when God would become true(fulfill) his talk(promise) to Ebraam, our people had become widely in IJif. \v 18 Then a new ruling man(king) who did not know about Josef became the ruling man(king) of Ijif. \v 19 He mistreated our people and destroyed our ancesters by forcing sent/ordered them to throw out their newborn baby to die.
\p
\v 20 At that time Moses was born and he looked a good child in God's eyes. In three months he was cared for in his father's house. \v 21 When he was put outside, Farawa's daughtor adopted him her son. \v 22 Moses was taught all the wisdom by Ijif people and he was really powerful in talk and action.
\p
\v 23 When Moses was 40 years old, he decided to visit his Israil people. \v 24 Moses saw Ijif man destroyed(mistreated) Israil man, so he came for the man's helping and avenging him, [and]killed the Ijif man. \v 25 Moses thought that his people might understand that God led him to save them, but they didn't understand. \v 26 The next day Moses came to see two Israil men fighting. He tried to make peace them between them by this talk, 'Men, you are friends, why are you hurt yourselves?'
\p
\v 27 But that man who spoiled his friend, he pushed Moses aside and said, "Who made you a ruler and judge over us? \v 28 Are you going to kill me like as you killed Ijif man yesterday?' \v 29 When Moses heard this talk, he went to the land of Midian and he became foreigner married and became with two sons.
\p
\v 30 Forty years later, a man carrying heavenly message(angel) appeared to Moses through the flame of bush fire in the desert near Mount name Sainai. \v 31 When Moses saw this fire, he was amazed. As he went close to see, he heard Lord's voice: \v 32 'I am the God whom your ancestors, Ebraam, Aisek and Jeikof, worshipped' Moses trembled with fear to look.
\p
\v 33 Then the Lord said to him, 'Take off your sandols, this place where you are standing is without.dust(holy) ground. \v 34 I have seen my people's suffering in Ijif in a long time. I have heard their crying sound and in this reason I came down to rescue them. Now go, I will send you to Ijif.
\p
\v 35 This was same Moses who they rejected with talk, 'Who made you our head man and judge?' God sent him leading them and saving them, through the man carrying heavenly message who appeared to him in the bush. \v 36 Moses brought them out of Ijif, did special workings(miracles) and surprising things in Ijif, at there Red Sea and for forty years in the desert.
\p
\v 37 This is the Moses who told the Israil people, 'God will send you.p a God's man who make know(prophet) like me from your people.' \v 38 He is the one who was with the people of Israil assembled in the desert; he was with our ancestors when the man carrying heavenly message who spoke to him on Mount Sainai, and he received God's living talks and passed on to us.
\p
\v 39 But our ancestors didn't obey him and they rejected him and wanted to return to Ijif.
\p
\v 40 They told Aron, 'Make us small gods who will be our head man. Because this man Moses who brought us out of Ijif, we don't know what has happened to him.'
\p
\v 41 On that day they made an lying idol like a cow. They brought sacrifice to it and had a feast in honor of what they made by their hands. \v 42 But God turned back from them and abandoned them/letted them go to worship the stars, moon and sun. This matches with what is written in the book of the God's people who make know(prophets),
\q1 'You Israil people! You didn't bring me sacrifices and offerings
\q2 during forty years in the desert.
\q1 \v 43 You have taken up the small canvas house of idol Molek
\q2 and your god of star Rèfan,
\q2 which idoles you worshipped.
\q1 So I will remove/send you into exile to Babilon.
\p
\v 44 "Our ancesters carried the canvas house(Tabernacle) where God say through the desert. It was made according to what God showed Moses. \v 45 Some years later, our ancestors received canvas house from their fathers when walked with Josuwa and took over the land from the nations which God removed before them. And it stayed there until the time of Deifid came. \v 46 Deifid knew God's favor and asked that I will prepare living place for God of Jeikof. \v 47 But Solomon came who built a house for him.
\p
\v 48 "But the Most High God does not live in houses built by human. As God's man who make know(prophet) says,
\q1 \v 49 "'The Lord says, "Heaven is my sitting place,
\q2 and this land is my footstool.
\q1 You are not able to built my house.
\q1 I don't need my resting place.
\q2 \v 50 My hands have made all the things.'
\p
\v 51 "You without-hearing people! You have hard heart and ears deaf to the true talk. You are just like your fathers. You have always oppose the God Spirit! \v 52 Your anscestors killed all God's men who make know(prophets)! Like that they killed them who spoke the coming of the Straight One, Keriso who you.p rejected and killed. \v 53 You are the ones who received God's law through men carrying heavenly message(angels) but you have not obeyed to do it!"
\s They hit Stifèn with stone
\p
\v 54 When Sifèn said that, Ju head men were angry and ground teeth. \v 55 But Stifèn was full of the God Spirit, looked up to heaven and saw God's strong light(glory), and Yesu standing at the right side of God. \v 56 He said, "Look, I see heaven opened and the Son of Man standing at the right side of God.
\p
\v 57 Then they put [their] hands over [their] ears and shouted loudly, every people rushed at him, \v 58 led him out of the town, and throw stones him. In this day the eye watching men(witnesses) took off their own outside clothes and put them at the feet of a young man Sol.
\p
\v 59 When they were stoning him, Stifèn talked with God, "Lord Yesu, receive my spirit." \v 60 Then Stifèn knelt and shouted, "Lord, forget their sin." When he said this, he died.
\c 8
\p
\v 1 Sol approved of their killing Stifèn.
\s Because of persecution of Yesu's family(church) they scatterd
\p
On that day a big persecution became wide to Jerusalem Yesu's family(church), all approving truth people were scattered through Judia and Samaria, but only men with Yesu's authority(apostles) stayed in Jerusalem. \v 2 God fearing men buried Stifèn in the land and were very sad. \v 3 But Sol was destroying the Yesu's family(church). He went from house to other house, he caught men and women, held them and put into darkness house.
\s Filif in Samaria
\p
\v 4 Those who were scattered and preached the talk wherever they were travelling. \v 5 Filif went to cities in Samaria region and preached about Keriso there. \v 6 When many people were listening to Filif and saw the surprising things he did, they were hearing well what he said. \v 7 Evil spirits went out from many people with a voice, a many paralyzed people and lame people became good(were healed). \v 8 So there was big joy in that city.
\s Saimon the sorcery man
\p
\v 9 There was a man name Saimon who did sorcery in the city and deceived them with surprising thing all the people in Samaria with surprising things. He boasted that he was with strong power, \v 10 and all the people in that city, with.power people and without.power people, they heard and said this talk like that, "This man is with strong power God gave this power to him." \v 11 They followed him because he did continually surprising things with sorcery. \v 12 But when they truly approved(believed) in Filif's teaching of good talk of God's kingdom and the name of Yesu Keriso, so men and women began to be baptized with water. \v 13 Saimon truly approved(believed) and was baptized. And he followed Filif everywhere, surprised by big surprising things and special workings(miracles) he saw.
\p
\v 14 When the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) in Jerusalem heard that the people of Samaria country had accepted God's talk, they sent Fitè and Jon to Samaria. \v 15 When they.d arrived, they.d talked with God for new approving truth people so that they.p will receive the God Spirit, \v 16 because the God Spirit had not yet come on those people, firstly they had been baptized by people in the name of Lord Yesu. \v 17 Fitè and Jon began to put their hands upon their.p head, they.p received God Spirit.
\p
\v 18 When Saimon saw that they received the God Spirit when men with Yesu's authority(apostles) laid their hands on people, he offered them.d money, \v 19 with talk that, "Give me this power so that anyone I lay my hands on people will also receive the God Spirit!"
\p
\v 20 Fitè answered him, "May your money be put to eternal fire(hell)with you, because you thought to buy the gift of God with money! \v 21 Here is no your place in this work, because your heart is not straight before God. \v 22 Turn away of this sin and start to talk with God to the Lord, maybe he forget what you have evil thought in your heart. \v 23 I see you are jealous man and bound by your sins."
\p
\v 24 Saimon answered him, "Start to talk with God to the Lord for me so that what you said will not happen to me.
\p
\v 25 After they.d told Lord's talk, Fitè and Jon went back to Jerusalem, preaching the good talk through many villages of Samaria.
\s Filif and Etiofia man
\p
\v 26 An man carrying heavenly message of the Lord said to Filif, "Go south road, that clear(desert) road from Jerusalem to Gasa." \v 27 So he began to walk, and on the middle he met Etiofia man, head man of watch of moneys of Kandake, its meaning ruling woman(queen) of the Etiopia. This man had gone to Jerusalem for worshipping, \v 28 and he went back to home was sitting in the chair horse carrier(carriot), he was reading the book of the God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya. \v 29 The God Spirit told Filif, "Go to this carriot and stay close to it."
\p
\v 30 Then Filif ran up to carriot and heard the man reading a book of Aisaya the God's man who make know(prophet). Filif asked him, "Do you understand what you are reading?"
\p
\v 31 He said, "How can I know, unless some man explains it to me?" So in this reason he allowed Filif to come up and to sit with him.
\p
\v 32 This part(passage) of Scripture he was reading,
\q1 "They led him like a sheep to killing,
\q2 and as a lamb before the fleece cutting people without-saying,
\q2 he did not open his mouth.
\q1 \v 33 They put him down and took his straight/justice away.
\q2 He was without.children, so no one can speak of his descendants.
\q2 Because his life was taken from the land."
\p
\v 34 The man asked Filif, "Tell me, who is the God's man who make know(prophet) talking, about himself or other man?" \v 35 So Filif began to preach with that passage of Scripture of Aisaya and told him the good talk about Yesu.
\p
\v 36 As they.d travelled along the road, they.d reached to some water and the man said, "Look, water is. I'd like to be baptized"{r{
\f...f* {r{8.37 
Some knowledge men think this: another part of this talk is here in this verse, but many knowledge men think not. This talk is, "Filif said to him, 'If you believe Yesu with all your heart, I can baptize you.' He answered, 'I believe that Yesu Keriso is the Son of God.'

 \v 38 And he said to driver to stop the chariot. Then Filif and the man went down into the water, and Filif baptized him. \v 39 When they.d came out of water, the Lord's Spirit suddenly took Filif away, and the eunuch did not see him again, but went on his way with joy. \v 40 But Filif arrived at Ajotus town and he went preached the good talk in all the towns until he arrived at Kaisaria.
\c 9
\s Sol's repentace from sins
\p
\v 1 Sol kept on start to kill the Yesu's following people. He went to the leading burning sacrifice man \v 2 and he asked him for letters to the meeting houses in Damaskos city, so that if he found any men and women who followed the Way of Yesu, he will take them immediately as darkness house men(prisoners) to Jerusalem. \v 3 When he became close Damaskos, suddenly a light from heaven flashed and surrounded him. \v 4 He fell to the ground and heard a sound of talk that, "Sol, Sol, why are hitting me?
\p
\v 5 Sol asked, "Lord, who are you?"
\p
He answered him, "I am Yesu, whom you are hitting. \v 6 Now get up and go into the city, and there is a man he will tell what you must do."
\p
\v 7 Those men were going through the road with Sol stood there speechless; they heard the sound of talk but did not see any[one]. \v 8 Sol got up from the ground, but when he opended his eyes he could not see anything. So they took him by the hand and led him to Damaskos. \v 9 For the three days he was blind, and did not eat or drink anything.
\p
\v 10 In Damaskos there was a following man name Ananias. The Lord called to him in a eye passover thing, "Ananias!"
\p
He answered him, "Yes, Lord."
\p
\v 11 The Lord told him, "Go to the Judas' house on Straight streets and asked for a man from Tarsus name Sol, there he is in talking with God. \v 12 In a eye passover thing he saw a man name Ananias came to him and [his]put hands and his [Sol's]eyes opened and got sight again."
\p
\v 13 Ananias answered him, "Lord, I've heard many talk about this man because he gave the pains to your people in Jerusalem. \v 14 And he came here with authority from the leading burning sacrifice man in order to arrest them all who says your name."
\p
\v 15 But the Lord said to Ananias, "Go! This man is my chosen to carry my talk to the Side people and their ruling men(kings) and to the people of Israil. \v 16 I will show him how bad he must feel for my name's sake."
\p
\v 17 So Ananias went and entered into the house. He put hands on Sol, he said, "Friend Sol, the Lord Yesu, who appeared to you on the road when you were coming here, he sent me so that you might see again and be filled with the God Spirit." \v 18 Immediately, something like a scale fell from Sol's eyes, and saw. He stood up and was baptized, \v 19 and after (he ate) his food and his strengh recovered.
\s Sol stayed in Damaskos and Jerusalem
\p
Sol stayed with the following men in Damaskos few days. \v 20 Immediatly he began to preach in the meeting houses that Yesu is the Son of God!" \v 21 All who heard him amazed and asked, "This man is the one who was killing Yesu's following people in Jerusalem. He came here to arrest following men as darkness house men(prisoners) to the leading burning sacrifice man. \v 22 Sol's preaching became very powerful and Ju people in Damaskos without.possible to answer to Fol because he showed Yesu is Keriso.
\p
\v 23 After many days, some of Ju people made plans to kill Sol, \v 24 but Sol learned of their thought/plan. Day and night they watched on the city gates to kill Sol. \v 25 But his following people took him at night and lowered Sol with a big basket from back of the town fence(wall).
\p
\v 26 When Sol came to Jerusalem, he tried to meet with the following men, but they were all afraid of him, they did not truly approve(believe) that he is already a following man. \v 27 But Banabas brought Sol to the men with Yesu's authority(apostles). Banabas told them how Sol saw the Lord on the road and how Lord said to him, and how he preached without.fear in the name of Yesu in Damaskos.
\p
\v 28 Sol stayed with men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and moved around without fear in Jerusalem, saying without fear in the name of the Lord. \v 29 Sol talked and argued with the Greek-speaking Ju people, but they tried to kill him. \v 30 When approving truth people learned of this, they took Sol to Kaisaria city and sent him away to Tarsus city.
\p
\v 31 Then the Yesu's family(church) throughout Judia, Galili region and Samaria, they enjoyed the peace in that time. There were strengh and encouragement of the God Spirit, many people added and lived with the fear of the Lord.
\s Enias and Dorkas
\p
\v 32 While Fitè went around some area, he went there to visit God's approving truth people to Lida village. \v 33 There he saw a man name Enias, paralyzed man who was paralyed for 8 years. \v 34 Fitè said to him, "Enias, Yesu Keriso will make you good. Get up and rolled up your mat." Immediately Enias stood up. \v 35 All those who lived in Lida and Saron, they saw him and began to turn into the Lord.
\p
\v 36 In Jofa city there was a following man(disciple) woman name Tabita, Greek name is Dorkas, who was always doing good things and helping the poor. \v 37 At that time woman felt sick and died, and they washed her body with water and laid it up in the house. \v 38 Lida village was near Jofa city, so when the following men heard that Fitè was in Lida village, they sent two men to him and told him, "Come quickly!"
\p
\v 39 Fitè returned with them, and when he arrived, they took him up into the house. All the widows surrounded him, crying and showing him clothes and other clothing which Dorkas made while she was still alive with them.
\p
\v 40 Fitè sent them all out from the inside of the room, then he knelt down and talked with God. Then he turned toward the dead woman, he said, "Tabita, get up." Immediately woman opened [her] eyes, and then woman saw Fitè and she sat up. \v 41 He hold her with hand and supported her get up. Then he called the approving truth people and wodows, showed them living woman. \v 42 The story about raising from the death became wide to all over Jofa city and many people truly approved(believed) in the Lord. \v 43 Fitè stayed in Jofa city for many days with a man [who] took the skin animal skin(tanner) name Saimon.
\c 10
\s Konelias called for Fitè
\p
\v 1 At Kaisaria city there was a man name Konelias, a Rom solidiers' headman who was taking care of 100 soldiers this name is Italia soldiers group. \v 2 He was God-fearing man with all his family and was worshipper; he gave things widely to those in need and always talked with God. \v 3 One day afternoon about three o'clock, he had a eye passover thing(vision). He saw a man carrying heavenly message(angel) of God, who came to him and said to him, "Konelias!"
\p
\v 4 Konelias saw him in fear and asked him, "What is this, Lord?"
\p
The man carrying heavenly message(angel) answered him, "God is pleased with your talking with God(prayers) and giving things to the poor. \v 5 Now send men to Jofa city to bring back a man name Saimon who people call other name Fitè. \v 6 He is staying with Saimon, a leather maker with animal skin(tanner), whose house is by the sea."
\p
\v 7 When the man carrying heavenly message(angel) who spoke to him disappeared, Konelias called his two without.payment working men(servants) and a God fearing soldier. \v 8 Konelias told them all what happened to him and sent them off to Jofa city.
\s Fitè saw eye passover thing(a vision)
\p
\v 9 The next day about noon Konelias's without.payment working men(servants) were on the way and coming near the town, Fitè went up on sitting place on the roof to talk with God. \v 10 There he felt hungry, and wanted something to eat, and while food were preparing, he saw a eye passover thing from God. \v 11 He saw the heaven opened and something looked like wide clothes coming down by 4 corners to the land. \v 12 In this wide clothes there were all different animals and animals crawling with belly(reptiles), and birds. \v 13 Then God said to him, "Get up, Fitè. kill and eat."
\p
\v 14 Fitè answered him, "No, Lord. I never eat somethings to bad to me."
\p
\v 15 God spoke to him again that, "No. You should eat it. Don't say that bad what God has made them good."
\p
\v 16 These things happened three times, and suddenly this clothe went back into heaven.
\p
\v 17 When Fitè was still confusing about the meaning of the eye passover thing(vision), the man sent by Konelias they asked where Saimon's house was and stopped at the gate of house. \v 18 They called, "Is there a guest here his name of Saimon Fitè?"
\p
\v 19 While Fitè was still thinking about the eye passover thing, the God Spirit said to him, "Saimon, three men are looking for you. \v 20 So get up and go down. Don't hesitate to go with them, because I have sent them."
\p
\v 21 Fitè came down and said to this men, "I am the man who you are looking for. Why have you come?"
\p
\v 22 These men answered him, "We came from Konelias Roman soldiers head man(the centurion). He is a straight and God-fearing man, who all the Ju people respect. A without.dust(holy)/holy man carrying heavenly message told him to send people to his house so that he can hear what you will say." \v 23 So Fitè invited these men to his house. So they became his guests.
\s Fitè there at Konelias's house
\p
The next day Fitè was preparing to go with them, and some of approving truth people from Jofa city went with them. \v 24 The next day he arrived at Kaisaria city. Konelias was waiting for him and called all his family and close friends. \v 25 When Fitè entered his house, Konelias met him and fell at his feet with respect[worshiped him]. \v 26 But Fitè caused/made him rise and said to him, "Got up, don't worship me. I'm definitely just as you are."
\p
\v 27 Fitè a Konelias were talking [together], after this Fitè went inside and found people group. \v 28 Fitè told them, "You Side people know well our Ju people's law, Ju people should not enter a outside man's house and should not associate with Side people. But God has shown me that I should not reject that you are bad or with dirty. \v 29 So when you.p sent for me, I came without question. I ask you.p, "Why did you.p call me?"
\p
\v 30 Konelias answered him, "Before four days I was talking with God in my house this time, 3 o'clock in the afternoon. Suddenly a man appeared with shining clothes in front of me. \v 31 And the man carrying heavenly message(angel) said, "Konelias, God heard your talking with God and remembered your giving things(gifts) to the poor. \v 32 Send people to Jofa city to Saimon who they call Fitè. He is a guest of Saimon animal skin tanning man, who is(lives) beside the sea.' \v 33 So I sent for you at once, and it was good of you to come. Now we are all here before God to listen every talk what the Lord sent you to tell us."
\p
\v 34 Then Fitè began to speak: "I now realize [that] it is true God does not show way only some part like \v 35 but accepted from every nation those who fear him and do what is straight. \v 36 You.p know the talk God sent to the people of Israil, preached the good talk of the peace through Yesu Keriso, who is Lord of all people. \v 37 You.p know what has happened throughout Judia, beginning in Galili region after the baptism Jon preached. \v 38 How God chose Yesu of Najaret with God Spirit and power, and how he went around doing good and healing all who were under the power of the Sáifèr(Satan), because God were.d with him.
\p
\v 39 We are watching men of everything he did in the land of Ju people and in Jerusalem. They killed him through that they hung him on a cross, \v 40 but God raised him from dead three days later to be seen, \v 41 all the people did not see him, but only watching men whom God appointed long time ago saw, that is, we ate and drink with him after he rose from dead. \v 42 He commanded us to preach to the people and to tell that he is the one who God appointed as judging man of the living and the dead. \v 43 All the prophers tell about him that every people who truly approves(believes) in him found he forget sins through his name."
\p
\v 44 While Fitè was still speaking these talk, the God Spirit came down to them all who heard this talk. \v 45 The Ju approving truth people who came with Fitè were amazed that the gift of the God Spirit in the same way had been poured out on the outside men, \v 46 because they heard them speaking in other talks(languages) and praising God.
\p
Then Fitè said, \v 47 "They had received the God Spirit just as we did. No one can stop them from being baptized with water." \v 48 Therefore told them be baptized in the name of Yesu Keriso. Then they asked Fitè to stay with them for a three/few days.
\c 11
\s Fitè explained his actions
\p
\v 1 The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and the approving truth people thoughout Judia region heard that the Side people also received the talk of God. \v 2 When Fitè went back to Jerusalem, Ju approving truth people rebuked him \v 3 and said, "You.s went to the house of Side people and ate food with them."
\p
\v 4 Fitè said all talk to them what had happened there from the beginning. \v 5 "I was in the town of Jofa in talking with God, and I saw a eye passover thing. I saw something like a wide clothes coming down from heaven by 4 corners, and it came down to where I was. \v 6 I looked into it [and] saw animals with 4 legs, wild animals, crawling animal with belly(reptiles) and birds. \v 7 I heard talk telling me that, "Get up, Fitè. Kill and eat them.'
\p
\v 8 I answered, "No, Lord. With dirty and with dust animal has not entered my mouth."
\p
\v 9 God said from heaven again, "No. You should eat it. Do not say what God has made them good." \v 10 This happened three times, and that clothes went up to heaven again.
\p
\v 11 Suddenly three men who had been sent from Kaisaria city stopped at the house where I was staying. \v 12 The God Spirit told me not hesitate to go with them. These 6 friends also went with me, and we entered Rom soldier's head man Konelias's house. \v 13 Konelias told us how he saw a man carrying heavenly message in his house and that man carrying heavenly message said, 'Send the people to Jofa town to Saimon who they called Fitè. \v 14 Fitè will carry you.p talk through which you and all your family/household will be saved.'
\p
\v 15 "As I began to speak, the God Spirit came to them in the same way how it came to us at first. \v 16 Then I remembered what Lord said, 'Jon baptized with water, but you.p will be baptized with the God Spirit.' \v 17 It is in the light(clear) that God gave them the same kind gift he gave us, who truly approved(believed) in the Lord Yesu Keriso; therefore I was not going to stop what God was doing.
\p
\v 18 When they heard this, they stopped objecting [and]only praising God, said, "So then God gave thought to the Side people to turn away from sins to life."
\s The Yesu's family(church) in Antiok city
\p
\v 19 Those who had been scattered by Stifèn's death went like as Fonesia, Saifras, and Antiok, telling talk to Ju people only. \v 20 But some people from Saifras and Sairene cities, went to Antiok and began to speak good talk to Side people about the Lord Yesu. \v 21 The Lord's hand was with them, and many Side people truly approved(believed) and turned from their sins to the Lord.
\p
\v 22 When the Yesu's family(church) in Jerusalem heard about this [that] many Side people turned to the Lord, so they sent Banabas to Antiok city. \v 23 When he arrived and saw God's blessing, he was in joy and he encouraged all of them to be true to the Lord with all their hearts. \v 24 Banabas was a good man, full of God Spirit and big mind(faith), he brought many people to the Lord.
\p
\v 25 Then Banabas went to Tarsus city to look for Sol, \v 26 and when he found Sol, Banabas brought him to Antiok city. For a whole year, Banabas and Sol met with Yesu's family(church) and taught many people. People called the following men first as Keriso's People(Christian)at Antiok city.
\p
\v 27 At that day some God's people who make know(prophets) came from Jerusalem to Antiok city. \v 28 One of them name Agabus stood up [and] through the God Spirit he said that a big famine would spread over Roman county. (This happened during the time when Klaudius was leading.) \v 29 The following men wrote mind(decided) to help their friends who lived in Judia area. \v 30 They collected the money and gave it to Banafas and Sol, who took it to the head men in Judia area.
\c 12
\s The man carrying heavenly message(Angel) took out Fite from darkness house
\p
\v 1 At that time the ruling man(king) Erod caught people from the Yesu's family(church), thinking to kill them. \v 2 Erod sent/ordered soldiers to kill Jems, the brother of Jon with a sword to death. \v 3 When Erod killed Jems make happy Ju people, so he also went to arrest Fitè. This happened during the festival of bread [made] without yeast. \v 4 After arresting, he put him in darkness house, guarding with 4 groups of soldiers which one group had 4 soldiers, totally 16 soldiers. Erod thought to bring him out for asking(trial) after the Passover feast.
\p
\v 5 So they put Fitè into darkness house, but the Yesu's family(church) was really big talking with God for him.
\p
\v 6 That same night Erod thought mind(decided) to bring him to the court, Fitè was sleeping between the two soldiers, with two chains, and some guards stood at the door. \v 7 Suddenly a man carrying heavenly message of the Lord appeared and a light shone into the darkness house. He struck Fitè on the side and woke him up and said, "Get up quickly!" and the chains fell off his hands.
\p
\v 8 Then the man carrying heavenly message(angel) said to him, "Tie/Put on your clothes and sandols." And Fitè did these things. The man carrying heavenly message said, "Put on your clothes and follow me." \v 9 Fitè followed him they.d went out of the darkness house, but he did not know what the man carrying heavenly message was doing but really happened; he thought it might be a eye passover thing. \v 10 They.d passed the first and second guarding people group and came to the iron gate which was road to the city. It opened them by itself for them.d, and they.d went through the road. When they had walked through that road, suddenly the man carrying heavenly message left him.
\p
\v 11 Fitè came back to his senses and said, Now I know without a doubt that the Lord has sent his man carrying heavenly message to rescue to me from Erod's hands and from every Ju people's hope."
\p
\v 12 When he realized this, he went Meri's house, the mother of the Jon Mak, where many people gathered for talking with God. \v 13 Fitè began to knock in the gate, and working girl name Roda came to answer it. \v 14 When girl recognized Fitè's voice, joy came surpassed her, she ran back quickly without opening door and told, "Fitè is at the door!"
\p
\v 15 They told her, "Your mind is tricking you." When she kept talking that it is true, they said, "It must be a man carrying heavenly message(angel) for helping him."
\p
\v 16 But Fitè kept on knocking. When they opened the door and saw Fitè, they were amazed. \v 17 Fitè motioned with hand for them to be quiet down and described them how the Lord had brought him out of darkness house. He said, "Tell Jems Yesu's younger brother and the other friends about this." And then he went to another place.
\p
\v 18 The next morning there was big counfusion among the soldiers what had happened to Fitè. \v 19 Later Erod tried to start to find Fitè but did not see him, he started to ask/court to the guards and put them to death.
\s Erod was died
\p
Then Erod went from Judia area to Kaisaria city so he stayed there. \v 20 He was angry to the people of Taire and Sidon country, so they went together to see Erod. Firstly they asked Blastus, the chief of guard of Erod's house in order to help them. Then they went to Erod and asked not keep on stopping food because the country of Taire and Sidon always were taking food from the ruling man Erod's country.
\p
\v 21 On the appointed day Erod dressed in his titlename cloth; sat on his ruling sitting place and gave a public talk(speech) to the people. \v 22 They shouted, "This is the voice of god, not of a man." \v 23 Immediately, because Erod did not give praise to God, so a man carrying heavenly message of the Lord struck him, so worms began to eat Erod and he died.
\p
\v 24 But the talk of God grew with healthy and became wide.
\p
\v 25 When Barabas and Sol had finished their.d work, they returned from Jerusalem to Antiok with Jon Mak.
\c 13
\s They sent Banabas and Sol
\p
\v 1 In the Yesu's family(church) of Antiok there were God's people who make know(prophets) and teaching men. They were Banabas, Saimon [called] black [skin]man, Luses from Sairia city, Manaen(who was close relatives of Erod), and Sol. \v 2 When they were worshiping the Lord with fasting, the God Spirit said, "Set apart Banabas and Sol for me for the work which I chose for them.d." \v 3 So after their fasting and talking with God, they laid hands on them and sent them.d off.
\s Fol and Banabas preached them good news at Saifrus
\p
\v 4 They two went on their way in the God Spirit, went to Selosia town and traveled to Saifrus town from there. \v 5 When they.d arrived to Salamis town, they.d began to preach the talk of God through the Ju meeting houses(meeting houses). They were with Jon [as]their helper.
\p
\v 6 They traveled around whole region until they arrived at Fafos village. There they met Bar-Yesu. He was a Ju sorcery man and false word telling man(prophet) name Bar-Yesu. \v 7 He worked for Sergius Faulus, who has many knowledge and was the head man of Rom soldiers in this land. Sergius Faulus wanted to hear the talk of God and he sent them to/for them Banabas and Sol. \v 8 But sorcery man Elimas(this is meaning of Bar-Yesu's name) told him and tried to turn away from the big mind(faith) of the big man. \v 9 Then Sol, who was also called Fol, filled with the God Spirit, looked straight him at Elimas and said, \v 10 "You are the child of Sáifèr and the fighting man(enemy) of all straight! You are full of all kinds of deceit and liers. Stop, do not turn away people from Lord's straight way with lying! \v 11 Now the Lord's anger will get you. You will be blind, and for a while you can't see the light of the sun.
\p
Immediately mist and darkness covered him, and he lost(was blind) then he was looking for someone to lead him by the hand. \v 12 When the Rom soldiers' head man saw what had happened, he was amazed at the teaching of the God's talk, he truly approved(believed) in the Lord.
\s Fol and Banabas preached them good news at Antiok city in Fisidia big area(district)
\p
\v 13 From Fafos, Fol and with his group traveled with big boat to Fargat in Famfila, but Jon left them and went back to Jerusalem. \v 14 From Fargata they went on to Antiok city in Fisidia big area. On the Safat they endered Ju people's meeting house(synagogue) and sat down. \v 15 After reading the law of Moses and the God's man who make know(prophet)'s talk, the head men of meeting house sent the talk to them, "Friends/Brothers, if you have any talk of encouragement for these people, please speak."
\p
\v 16 Fol stood, lift up his hand and said, "People of Israil and you Side people who worship God, listen to me! \v 17 The God of the Israil people chose our ancesters and made the people wide during their staying in Ijif, and God took them out and led from that country with his power, \v 18 he kept on enduring their sins until 40 years in the desert, \v 19 he destroyed 7 nations in the land of Kanan and gave the land and make them become the owners. \v 20 All of this way took about 450 years.
\p
"After this, God gave them head men for judging(judges) until came the time of the God's man who make know(prophet) Samuel. \v 21 The people asked for the ruling man(king), and he gave them Sol son of Kis, from the tribe of Benjamin, who ruled 40 years. \v 22 But God removed Sol and he made Deifid their the ruling man(king). He said about him, "I found Deifid son of Jesi, this man who is with my heart, he will do everything I want him to do.'
\p
\v 23 From this man's family God has brought to Israil poeple the life saving Man(Savior) Yesu, as he said without lying talk(promise). \v 24 Before appearing of Yesu, Jon first preached turning away from sin and washing with water(baptism) to the all the people of Israil. \v 25 When Jon was finishing his work, he said, 'Who do you think I am? I am not Keriso. But he is coming after me, whose sandols I am not enough to untie.'
\p
\v 26 "Friendly/Brothers, Ebraam's children, and you God fearing Side people, they sent this mssage of salvation to us. \v 27 The people in Jerusalem and their head men did not recognized Yesu as the one the God's people who make know(prophets) had spoken about. But they started to kill Yesu, [and] this talk became true what the God's people who make know(prophets) said which are read every Safat. \v 28 They could not find the reason for his death, but they asked Failet to kill him.
\p
\v 29 When they had done all in this books which were written about him, they took him down from the cross and put him in a grave house. \v 30 But God raised him from death, \v 31 and for many days he appeared to those who hade traveled with him from Galili region to Jerusalem. They are now his eyes.watching men to the people of Israil.
\p
\v 32 We tell you.p the good talk, what God said without lying talk(promise) to our ancestors \v 33 God has done(fulfilled)for us, for their descendants, by raising up Yesu. As it is written in the second Sams buk,
\q1 'You are my Son,
\q2 today I have become your Father.'
\p
\v 34 God raised him from death, then will not be decayed, what he said in this talk,
\q1 "I will give the without.dust(holy) and true blessing what had said to Deifid."
\p
\v 35 In another Sams buk it is written,
\q2 "You will not allow your Without.dust Son to be rotten."
\p
\v 36 "When Deifid did God's work to his generation, he died, he was buried with his ancestors and his body spoiled. \v 37 But the one man who God raised from death did not be spoiled.
\p
\v 38 "Therefore, my brothers, I want you.p to know that through Yesu the forgetting of sins is told to you.p. \v 39 Who truly approves(believes) in Yesu, God will call him straight man, it won't by the law of Moses. \v 40 Be careful! Don't let which thing the God's people who make know(prophets) have said happen to you.p,
\q1 \v 41 " You people [who are]rejecting God, will die in wondering ,
\q2 because I will do something in your days
\q2 [that] you would not truly approve(believe),
\q2 even though someone will tell you."
\p
\v 42 As Fol and Banabas left the Ju people's meeting house, the people invited them.d to speak again on the next Safat. \v 43 When crowds was spreading, many of Ju people and outside men followed Fol and Banabas, who talked with them and urged them to stay in the grace of God.
\p
\v 44 On the next Safat almost every people in town gathered to hear the talk of the Lord. \v 45 When Ju people saw the crowds, they were filled with jealousy and began to argue against what Fol said. \v 46 Then Fol and Banabas answered them withour fear, "We have to speak the talk of God to you Ju people first. Because you reject it and judge yourselves are not able to to receive eternal life, we.d will leave you.p and go the Side people. \v 47 The Lord gave us this ,
\q1 I have made you a light to them the Side people,
\q2 in order that you will take salvation to the ends of the earth."
\p
\v 48 When the Side people heard this talk, they were in joy and gave thanks the Lord for the talk; and all who [God] chose for eternal life truly approved(believed)."
\p
\v 49 The talk of the Lord became wide through the whole region. \v 50 But Ju people began to be against head men in the city and God fearing big women. They started a persecution against Fol and Banabas and threw them out of their region. \v 51 So in this reason they.d shook the dust from their feet as a warning to them and went to Ikonium village. \v 52 And the following people were filled with joy and with the God Spirit.
\c 14
\s Fol and Banafas preached the good talk to the Ikonium people
\p
\v 1 At Ikonium area Fol and Banabas continually went to the Ju people's meeting house. There they.d spoke strongly to a big number of Ju people and Side people [so] they truly approved(believed) God. \v 2 But these Ju people who rejected to truly approve(believe) God said to the Side people and were spoiling their mind to began to be against Fol and Banafas. \v 3 So Fol and Banabas stayed there a long time, spoke for the Lord without fear, and the Lord himself made clear that the talk of the grace is true by they.d were doing showing things(signs) and surprising things(wonders). \v 4 The people of the city were divided; some with the Ju people, other people with the people with Yesu's authority. \v 5 Then Side people and Ju people gathered together with their head men in order to kill Fol and Banabas. \v 6 When the (two)men with Yesu's authority(apostles) knew about it, they.d fled to the cities of Likonia in Listra and Derbe country and the other close area, \v 7 there they started again to preach the good talk.
\s Fol and Banafas preached the good talk In Listra and Derbe city
\p
\v 8 In Listra city there was a man crippled, who had been lame from birth and had never walked. \v 9 He listened to Fol's talk. Fol was looking directly him, saw that he had big mind(faith) to become good \v 10 and called out, "Stand up straightly with your feet!" Immediately the man jumped up and began to walk.
\p
\v 11 When the crowds saw the surprising thing what Fol did, they shouted with Likonia language, "Two real gods have came down to us like men!" \v 12 Banabas they call Jeus, its meaning in Greek language big God and Fol they called Ermes, its meaning in Greek language is word head man. \v 13 Jeus's worshipping house was outside the city, burning sacrifice men(priest) brought cows and flowers to the city gates because he and the crowds wanted to offer sacrifices to them.
\p
\v 14 But when the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) Banabas and Fol heard about this, they.d tore their clothes and ran out among the people, shouting, \v 15 "Friends, why are you.p doing this? We are only human, just like you.p are. We have come to bring you good talk, in order to turn from these without.meaning ways to the living God, who made the heaven, the earth and the sea and everything in these. \v 16 A long time ago he allowed all the people to go by their own will, \v 17 but he never left them forever but he showed good ways continually by giving you rain from heaven and food in their season and he kept on providing you with plenty of food and filled your hearts with joy." \v 18 Even with these talks, Fol and Banabas caused the crowds not to offer a sacrifice to them, but it was not easy to block them from doing it.
\p
\v 19 Then some Ju people came from Antiok and Ikonium city and directed people to kill Fol and Banabas. They hit Fol with stone and dragged him, took him from the city, thought he might die. \v 20 But after this following men surrounded Fol, he got up and went back into the town. The next day Fol and Banabas went to Derbe city.
\s Fol and Banabas went back to Antiok in Siria
\p
\v 21 They preached the good talk in Derbe city and many people became following men. Then they went back to Listra, Ikonium and Antiok, \v 22 strengthened following men and encouraged them in order that they continue to be in true big mind(faith)(faith). They.d said, "We must go through many troubles continually to enter the ruling of God." \v 23 Fol and Banabas appointed Yesu's family(church) helpers(head people) for them in each Yesu's family(church). With talking with God and fasting, they committed them to the Lord in whom they had put their hope. \v 24 After going through Fisidia area, they came to Famfilia area, \v 25 and they.d started to preach in Ferga area, after that they.d went to Atalia city.
\p
\v 26 From Atalia they went back to Antiok by big boat(ship). Antiok was the place where before believers gave/committed them to God's grace hand to do God's work. These two people completed the work which was given to them. \v 27 They.d arrived at Antiok, they.d gathered Yesu's family(church) and told all what God had done through them and how God had opened the door of big mind(faith) to the Side people. \v 28 And they.d stayed there a long time with following men.
\c 15
\s Church head men' meeting at Jerusalem
\p
\v 1 Some men came from Judia to Antiok and was teaching approving truth people: "If you didn't be cut your skin(circumcised), as Moses's law said, you cannot be saved." \v 2 This teaching caused/brought Fol and Banabas arguing with this teaching. Fol and Banabas were appointed with other approving truth people, to go to Jerusalem to see the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and other head people about this teaching. \v 3 The Yesu's family(church) sent Fol and Banabas through Fonisia and Samaria, and they.d told how the Side people had turned [to God]. This talk made all approving truth people to be happy. \v 4 When they.d arrived at Jerusalem, Yesu's family(church) and men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and other head people welcomed Fol and Banabas, to whom they.d told everything what God had done through them.(d).
\p
\v 5 Then some of approving truth people who belonged to Farasi group stood up and said, "The Side people must be cut skin(circumcised) just as the law of Moses said."
\p
\v 6 The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and other head people gathered together because of this teaching. \v 7 After long debating this teaching, Fitè stood and said to them: "Friends/Brothers, you know that a long time ago God appointed me among you in order that Side people might hear good talk from my lips and truly approve(believe). \v 8 God, who knows people's heart, showed that he approved Side people by giving them the God Spirit just as he gave it to us. \v 9 He split.mind(planed) to make us one with Side people, because he wiped their hearts by big mind(faith). \v 10 So you.p should not put God in test by puting them today by carrying difficulty to the side approving truth people in the same way to our ancesters and to us that we cannot take them. \v 11 We truly approve(believe) and saved through the grace of our Lord Yesu, just as they are."
\p
\v 12 The people group became silent as they heard Banabas and Fol telling about miraculous showing things(signs) and surprising things(wonders) what God had done through them to the Side people. \v 13 When Banabas a Fol finished the talk, Jems stood with talk: "Friends, listen to me. \v 14 Saimon Fitè explained us how God first showed his mind how he made Side people for him. \v 15 And this conversion of Side people is exactly what God's people who make know(prophets) said. As it is written:
\q1 \v 16 "After this I will go back
\q2 and restore the kingdom of Deifid.
\q1 I will build again its ruins,
\q2 and I will make it again,
\q1 \v 17 so that all the people will seek the Lord,
\q2 including Side people who lift up my name,
\p
the Lord says, who made these things
\q2 \v 18 which they knew long times ago.
\p
\v 19 Therefore my thought is that we should not make it difficult them to cut skin for the Side people who turned to God. \v 20 But we should write a letter for them and tell them not to eat food which were from the idols' place, not to have sexual relation out of marriage, not to eat the animal which is not drained blood and not to eat blood. \v 21 Because they were preaching the law of Moses in every city from the ancient times and read them in the meeting houses on every Safat."
\s The letter for them to the side approving truth people
\p
\v 22 Then the men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and the head people together with whole Yesu's family(church) decided to choose their people to go to Antiok with Fol and Banabas. They chose Judas who is called Barsabas and Sailès, these men.d were head men among the approving truth people. \v 23 Through them they sent the following letter:
\p
"The men with Yesu's authority(apostles) and head people, your friends in Jerusalem,
\p
To the side approving truth people in Antiok , Siria and Silisia:
\p
Greetings.
\p
\v 24 We have heard that some went out from us without our knowing and spoiled your minds by what they said. \v 25 So we all agreed [and]chose some men and send them to you.p with our with heart(dear) brothers Banabas and Fol, \v 26 men/men.d who put.d to danger their/their.d lives for the name of Lord Yesu Keriso. \v 27 Therefore we are sending Judas and Sailès to you in order that they will confirm by [talk of] mouth what we are writing.
\p
\v 28 The God Spirit and we have agreed that we will not give difficult things but only few things: \v 29 You must leave from food which was from Idols' place, from blood, and from animal/meat without bleeding blood, from outside sex(sex out of marriage). It is good you.p stop these things.
\p
That's all.
\p
\v 30 They sent the men off and they went down to Antiok area. There they gathered the Yesu's family(church) together and there gave them the letter. \v 31 When people read it and were in joy for this encouraging talk. \v 32 Judas and Sailès, who were God's people who make know(prophets), said big encouraging and powerful talk to the approving truth people. \v 33 After some days there, Friends/brothers sent off Judas a Sailès with blessing and greeting to go back to those who sent them. 34-35\~
But Fol and Banabas stayed more there in Antiok, where they and with many people preached and taught the talk of the Lord.
\s Fol and Banabas divided
\p
\v 36 At another later time Fol said to Banabas, "Let us.d go.d back to [there] and visit.d the approving truth people in every towns where we preached.d the talk of Lord and see.d what they are doing." \v 37 Banabas wanted to take Jon Mak with them, \v 38 but Fol did not think that they will take him, because Jon Mak left them in Famfilia area and stopped from working. \v 39 There they had a big argument, and they seperated. Banabas took Mak and traveled by big boat(ship) to Saifras, \v 40 but Fol chose Sailès and the approving truth people gave.d them into the grace of the Lord. Then two of them left.d. \v 41 They went.d through Siria and Silisia area, they were speaking.d talk to give strength to the Yesu's families(churches).
\c 16
\s Timoti joined Fol and Sailès
\p
\v 1 Fol came to Derbe city and next to Listra city, where a following man(disciple) name Timoti lived. His mother was Ju woman and man/woman who truly approve, but his father was a Greek man. \v 2 The approving truth people spoke well of Timoti in Listra and Ikonium. \v 3 Fol wanted to walk/trip with him, so he cut skin(circumcised) him because of the Ju people who lived in that area, because they all knew that his father was a Greek. \v 4 Their trip was from one town to other town, they urged the belivers to follow the letter which Yesu's authority and other head people in Jerusalem wrote. \v 5 So the Yesu's familys(churches) became with strength in the big mind(faith) and grew [in number] every day.
\s Fol's eye passover thing of the man of Makedonia
\p
\v 6 Fol went with his group throughout the region of Frigia and Galasia, the God Spirit didn't allow them preaching the talk in the Esia region. \v 7 They came arrived to the border of Masia, they wanted to enter Biténia, but Yesu's Spirit did not allow them to enter. \v 8 So they passed by Masia and went to Troas. \v 9 That night Fol saw the eye passover thing of a man of Makedonia standing and begging him, "Come to Makedonia big area to help us." \v 10 After Fol's seeing the eye passover thing, we got ready quickly to go to Makedonia. Because we knew that God called us to preach the good talk to them there.
\s Lidias turns form sin in Filifi
\p
\v 11 We traveled by big boat(ship) from Troas to Samotras, and the next day arrived to Neafolis. \v 12 From there we went to Filifi, a Roman with mind(important) area and ruling city of that big area of Makedonia. We stayed there many days.
\p
\v 13 On the Safat we went out of the city gate to the river, with this thought there will be a place of talking with God. We sat down and began to speak to the women who had gathered there. \v 14 One woman who heard us her name was Lidia, who was from the city of Tayatira. She was a dealer in purple cloth and she was a worshipping woman of God. The Lord opened her heart to hear to Fol's talk. \v 15 Woman and her family were baptized, after that she invited us to her house. Woman said, "If you.p think that I am a true truly approving man(believer) in the Lord, come to my house and stay." So woman asked us, so we stayed there.
\s They put.d Fol and Sailès into Jail
\p
\v 16 One day we were going to the place of talking with God, we met a without.payment working girl(servant girl) who said about the future with the power of evil spirit. She found/earned big money from people because she said about future. She gave money to his own looking.after people(owners) \v 17 This girl followed Fol and us with talk that, "These men are without.payment working people(servants) of the Most High God, who are telling to you the saving way." \v 18 Girl kept do this for many days. Finally Fol became angry and turned and said to the spirit, "In the name of Yesu Keriso you to come out of her!" Immediately the spirit left girl.
\p
\v 19 When without.payment woking girl's owners recognized that the way to find money finished, they began to hit Fol and Sailès and dragged them into the marketplace to the head people. \v 20 They brought them before the governor of this area and said, "The men are.d from Ju, and they.d confused people, \v 21 they.d are teaching people different talk which is not straight for us Romans seem to do.
\p
\v 22 The crowd combined in thier striking Fol and Sailès, and the judging man of this big area ordered them tore their clothes and whipped. \v 23 Then they whipped them.d several whipping, and they were put them.d in darkness house, and they said to the darkness house guarding man to guard them.d carefully. \v 24 When he heard this order, he threw into two men and stocked their feet by woods.
\p
\v 25 In midnight Fol and Sailès were paraying and singing to God, and other [who] were in darkness house listened song. \v 26 Suddenly big earthquake shook the posts of the darkness house. At once all the darkness house doors were opened and every people's chains fell off.
\p
\v 27 The darkness house guarding man woke up, and when he saw the darkness house doors open, he drew this sword and about to kill himself because he thought the darkness house men(prisoners) might have escaped. \v 28 But Fol shouted, "Don't spoil yourself! We are all still here!"
\p
\v 29 The darkness house guarding man called for lights and after they brought right, he ran into the darkness house and fell down with trembling before Fol and Sailès. \v 30 Then he brought them.d out and asked, "Bigmen, what must I do to be saved?"
\p
\v 31 They.d answered him, "Believe in the Lord Yesu, and that time you will be saved with your family." \v 32 Then they told the talk of the Lord to him and to all the other people in his house. \v 33 At that night darkness house guarding man took them and washed their wounds; then immedately he and his family were baptized. \v 34 The darkness house guarding man brought them into his house and set a meal; he was filled with joy because he truly approved(believed) in God with his whole family.
\p
\v 35 When it was daybreak, Rom court workers(magistrates) sent/ordered their workers to the darkness house guarding man, "Let those men.d go out." \v 36 The darkness house guarding man told Fol, "The Rom court workers(magistrates) said that you and Sailès will go out. Now you.d leave this place and go in peace."
\p
\v 37 But Fol said to the working people: "They beat us.d pubicly without a court/trail, even though we.d are Roman citizens, and threw us into darkness house. Now do they want to go out us quietly? No! They themselves must come and let us.d out."
\p
\v 38 When workers told to the governors that Fol and Sailès were Roman citizens, they were full of fear. \v 39 They came to them.d with apologizing talk and led them.d out of the darkness house, asked them to leave town. \v 40 After Fol and Sailès came out of the darkness house, they.d went to Lidia's house, where they met the approving truth people and encouraged them. Then they.d left.
\c 17
\s Fol and Sailes preached good news In Tesalonika
\p
\v 1 When Fol and his companions passed through Amfifolis and Afolonia, they came to Tesalonika, there was a Ju meeting house. \v 2 There was his customs, Fol went into the meeting house, and on three Safat he began to discuss with the people, \v 3 a explained the Buk(scripture)s that Keriso had to be in suffering and rose from death. He said, "This Yesu is Keriso about whom I am preaching to you." \v 4 Some of Ju people truly approved(believed) and joined Fol and Sailès. There were many God fearing Side people and many head women.
\p
\v 5 But other Ju people were jealous, so they gathered bad acting people group in the marketplace, started chasing/arguing (each other) in the city. They went to Joson's house to find Fol and Sailès to bring them to the crowd. \v 6 But when they did not find Fol and Sailès, they forced Jason and other approving truth people before the governor of the city, with this voice, "These men who caused trouble all over the world now are here, \v 7 and Jason allowed them into his house. They who all broke the law of Roman Imperor Kaisar with saying that Yesu is another ruling man(king)." \v 8 When they heard this talk, the crowd and governors of the city they were angry. \v 9 Then they made Jason and other approving truth people pay money to be release.
\s Fol and Sailès preached good news in Berea
\p
\v 10 That very night, some approving truth people sent Fol and Sailès to Berea town. On Fol and Sailès arriving, they went to the Ju people's meeting house. \v 11 Because the Ju people of Berea were very good, their.p behaviour surpassed the Tesalonaika area people, they received the talk with joy and examined the Buk(scripture)s every day, were looking for [if] what Fol said true. \v 12 Many Ju people truly approved(believed) in talk and other big name women and other Greek men [did]
\p
\v 13 When Ju people in Tesalonika learned that Fol was preaching the talk of God in Berea, some people also went there and started arguing crowds and were congusing them.
\p
\v 14 At once the approving truth people sent Fol to the sea area, but Sailès and Timoti stayed in Berea. \v 15 When those people escort Fol to Aten, Fol said to them that, "Sailès and Timoti should join us quickly." Then they left.
\s Fol preached good news in Aten
\p
\v 16 While Fol is waiting for Sailès and Timoti in Aten city , he was without joy, because saw that city was full of idols. \v 17 He started discussing with Ju people in the Ju people's meeting house(synagogue) and God-fearing Side people. He also went to the marketplace everyday and he talked to the people there. \v 18 There were two groups, one of Efikuria group and other people of Stoik group with big knowledge(philosophy) began to discussing with him. Some asked, "What is this nonsence talking?" Others said, "He seems to be preaching about other gods." They said this talk because Fol preached good talk about Yesu and his rising. \v 19 They took him the head men's meeting name Areofagus, where they said to him, "Would you tell us knowldge what new teaching you are preaching? \v 20 You brought us different teaching we heard, and we want to know what is this meaning." \v 21 (All the Aten people and the people from other region who lived there spent time only sitting for talking and listening to the latest messages.)
\p
\v 22 So Fol stood up head men's meeting place name Areofagus and said, "People of Aten! I see you are worshipping (to)many gods very much. \v 23 Because when I walked around even found your worshipping things. I saw the shelter(alter) with this name: To without. knowing God. You don't know it to what you are worshipping, now I will tell you about him.
\p
\v 24 "The God made the world and everythings in it. Because he rules over all things in heaven and on earth, he does not live in the worshipping houses built by man's hands. \v 25 And he is not expecting/looking for this thing [which] people made for him, because he himself is life giver to all the people's and everything. \v 26 In the beginning God made/created one man, from him God created all the people who now live all the place in the world. And he also decided where each people group should live and how long they should live there. \v 27 God wanted people to search for him. Because he is not far from us, then they might seek him and find him.
\q1 \v 28 'Because by his power we live and move and exist.'
\p
As your people who know meaning of letter, they said,
\q1 'We are his children.'
\p
\v 29 Because we are God's children, we should not think that people can make God from gold and silver or stone with their knowledge. \v 30 In the past when people did not know what God wanted them to do, God did not put them into pain because they have no knowledge, but now God says every people everywhere to turn away from sins. \v 31 God has appointed a day when he will judge the world. He has appointed a man to judge us straightly. God has shown this man, whom God has appointed to judge the world, he is able to judge the world because God raised him from death."
\p
\v 32 When they heard about a man's rising from the death, some made fun of him, but some said, "We want you talk to us again about this talk's meaning." \v 33 After this meeting Fol left. \v 34 Some people became followers of Fol and truly approve(believe). Among them was Dionisus, who was from the group of Areofagus, also woman name Damaris and also other people.
\c 18
\s Fol preached the good news in Korint
\p
\v 1 After this, Fol left Aten city and went to Korint city. \v 2 There he met a Ju man name Akwila from Fontus. He came from Italia with his wife Frisila, because Rom high leading man(Emperor) Kaisar Klaudias said, "You Ju people, you.p should leave Rom." Fol went to see Akwila a Frisila, \v 3 because Fol was a canvas huose making man(tentmaker) as they were, Fol srayed and worked with them. \v 4 Every Safat Fol discuss with them in meeting house, in order that he make heart soft(convince) the Ju people and Side people.
\p
\v 5 When Sailès and Timoti arrived from Makedonia, here Fol was trying to make known Ju people that Yesu was Keriso. \v 6 But Ju people opposed Fol and said to wicked talk. So he shook the dust from his clothes and said, "If God put you in suffering/pain, it will be your fault, not my fault. From now I will go to the Side people."
\p
\v 7 Then Fol left the Ju people's meeting house and went to next house, to Taitus Jèstus' house who was a worshipper of God. \v 8 Krisfus, the head man of Ju people's the meeting house, and his family truly approved(believed) in the Lord and many of Korint people who heard him, truly approved(believed) and we baptized them.
\p
\v 9 One night the Lord said to Fol in a eye passover thing, "Don't be afraid, keep on talking, do not be silent and not stop. \v 10 Because I am with you, and someone cannot make stop and spoil/harm you, because there are many my people in this city." \v 11 In this reason Fol stayed in Korint for a year and a half he taught them the talk of God.
\p
\v 12 When Galio became governor of Akaya big area, some Ju people got together to stop Fol and brought him to the court. \v 13 They said, "This man is leading the people to worship God in different way in this way he broke our law."
\p
\v 14 Fol was about to speak, Galio said to ju people, "If you Ju people made a complaint about this problem, show me well, I will listen to you.p. \v 15 But this included about a question of speakings and names and your.p law, settle/solve this things by yourselves. I will not be in your.p court about this things. \v 16 So he took/sent them off from the court. \v 17 Then they all caught/hold Sostenes the Ju people's meeting house leading man [and] began to beat him in front of the court. But Galio did not think about it.
\s Frisila, Akwila and Afolos
\p
\v 18 Fol stayed on with the believers in Korint for many days. Then he left the people who truly opprove(believers) there, and went with Frisila and her husband Akwila. They went down to Sensèri. There Fol had his head shaved in order to follow his without.lying(promise) to God. Then they went to Siria area with big bout. \v 19 They stopped at Efesos city, Fol left Frislia and Akwila. He himself went into the Ju people's meeting house and was discussing with Ju people. \v 20 When they asked him to stay with them, [but] he declined. \v 21 But when Fol left, he said without lying talk(did without-lying talk), "I will come back in the God's willing." Then he left Efesos and was coming to Kaisaria. \v 22 When he arrived at Kaisaria area, he went to Jerusalem and gave a greeting the Yesu's family(church), and went back to Antiok area.
\p
\v 23 After staying some days, Fol walked from Antiok around the region of Galatia area and Frigia area, gave strength to all the following men.
\p
\v 24 Ju people name Afolos from Aleksandria region, came to Efesos. He was with the knowledge of the Buk(scripture). \v 25 He taught the way of the Lord, spoke with buring heart and taught about Yesu well, but he knew only the baptism of Jon. \v 26 He began to speak without.fear in the Ju people's meeting house. When Frisila and Akwila heard him, they invited him to their house and explained to Afolos the way of God straightly.
\p
\v 27 When Afolos wanted to go to Akaya big area, friends encouraged him and wrote the letter to the following men in Akaya big area to accept him. In his arriving, he became a big help to those who had truly approved(believed) through God's grace. \v 28 He discussed with the Ju people in public, he tried to put clearly from the Buk talk(Scripture) that Yesu was Keriso.
\c 19
\s Fol speaks in Efesos about Yesu
\p
\v 1 While Afolos was in Korint city, Fol walked through the bank/interior and he arrived at Efesos city. There he found some following men \v 2 and he asked them, "Did you.p receive the God Spirit when you truly approved(believed) Yesu?"
\p
They answered him, "No, we did not hear that there is a God Spirit."
\p
\v 3 So Fol asked them, "What baptism did you.p receive?"
\p
They answered him, "Jon's Baptism."
\p
\v 4 Fol said, "Jon's baptism was to turn from sins. Jon told the people to truly approve(believe) Yesu, who was coming after him." \v 5 On hearing this, baptized them in the name of Lord Yesu. \v 6 When Fol placed his hands on them, the God Spirit came to them, and they spoke with other talks(languages) and proclaimed God's talk. \v 7 There were perhaps 12 men.
\p
\v 8 Fol went into the Ju people's meeting house and spoke without fearing there for three months. He was discussing with them and tried to cause to truly opprove(believe) about ruling of God. \v 9 But some men became heart-harden(stubborn); they rejected to truly approve(believe) and publicly said evil talk about the way of God. So for this reason Fol left them. He took the following men with him [and] discussed everyday in the teaching house of Taranus. \v 10 He spend two years in talk, so that all Ju people and Side people who lived in Esia heard the talk of Lord.
\p
\v 11 God gave Fol the power to do special workings(miracles). \v 12 People put handkerchiefs or clothes that Fol touched to the sick people, they became good and evil spirits were going out.
\p
\v 13 Some Ju people went [and] tried to chase out evil spirits in the name of Lord Yesu over those who evil spirit possessed. One [of them] said, "In the name of Yesu, whom Fol preaches, I command, "Come out." \v 14 A Ju chief burning sacrifice men(chief priest) Skefa's seven sons were doing this work. \v 15 One day the evil spirit answered them, "I know Yesu and I know Fol, but who are you.p?" \v 16 Then the man with the evil spirit jumped on them and chased them all and beated them. They ran from the house naked and bleeding.
\p
\v 17 There Efesos when the Ju people and Side people in the Efesos heard about this, they were afraid, they honored Lord Yesu's name. \v 18 Many who bacame truly appove people(believers) started to report(confess) their evil things. \v 19 Some people who learned/practiced sorcery they brought thier sorcery books and burned them publicly. When they counted the price of people's books was several million kina. \v 20 So the talk of the Lord became widely and became with power.
\p
\v 21 After all this had happened, Fol decided to go to Makedonia and Akaya and Jerusalem. Fol said, "After that I must go to Rom." \v 22 So he sent his two helpers, Timoti and Erastus, to Makedonia, but he stayed more in Esia.
\s Trouble in Efesos
\p
\v 23 At that time trouble developed in Efesos because of God's Way. \v 24 There was a man name Demetrios, who made silver models of the worshipping house of the Artemis the goddess. Those who worked they found/earned a lot of money. \v 25 Demetios gathered his workers and said, "Friends, listen, you.p know we find/earn a lot of money for this work. \v 26 You.p have seen and knew how Fol has make them inside softly/convinced and led many people to other teaching in Efesos city and through whole Esia area. He said that gods made by man are not god. \v 27 This thing is without.joy because our way to find money will finish. Like that the worshipping house of the big woman god Atemis will be without.meaning, to whom they worship in Esia and the world. People will not think that the woman god Atemis is god."
\p
\v 28 When they heard this talk, they were angry and started shouting like with talk, "Great is big woman god Artemes of Efesos." \v 29 The city joined and shouted because there were one mind. People grabbed Gayus and Aristakus, Fol's travelling friends came from Makedonia area, and people forced them to the meeting place. \v 30 Fol wanted to go meeting place, but following men did not allow him to go to there. \v 31 Some government workers who were Fol's friends, they sent talk him urgently not to go to the meeting place.
\p
\v 32 The crowds were wondering because they were various shouting. Many people did not know the reason/why they were there. \v 33 The Ju people sent Aleksandè to them to say. He motioned for silence with hand. He wanted to tell them that Ju people had not developed the problem. \v 34 But when they realized that he was a Ju, they were shouting for two hours like that, "Big is Atemis of the Efesos!"
\p
\v 35 A city government working man stopped them and said, "People of Efesos, You.p know that the city of Efesos is guarding man of the worshipping house of the big woman god Artemis and this woman's face image came down from heaven. \v 36 Nobody can say that she did not come down from heaven. Be calm. Do not rush into anything. \v 37 You brought these men here, they did not say badly to our god and they did not steal anything from our god's worshipping house. \v 38 Then if Demetrius and his worker have a case against them, the court are open and there are a judge. They can say about this things. \v 39 If there are more complaint, they take to the court. \v 40 And so we know, that if head people hear what we did today, they will still talk to us about creating big trouble. We did it without.reason, so what we will say if they ask us about this. " \v 41 After saying this, he sent people.
\c 20
\s Fol traveled through Makedonia and Grik country
\p
\v 1 When the noising ended in the city, Fol went to the following people, and encouraged them. Then he said, "Goodbye" and went to Makedonia region. \v 2 He traveled through those regions, after speaking many talks of encouragement to the people Fol arrived in Grik country, \v 3 there he stayed three months. He decided to go back with big boat(ship) to Siria region, but he heard that some Ju people decided to kill him. So he decided to return through land [through] Makedonia. \v 4 Sofata Firus's son from Berea area, Aristakus and Sekudus from Tesalonika area, Gaius from Derbe area, Timoti also, Tukikus and Trofimus from province of Eisia went with Fol. \v 5 These men went on ahead and waited for us at Traus town. \v 6 But we came from Filifi city after the Festival of without.yeast bread. 5 days later we joined them at Traus city, where we stayed 7 days.
\s Yutikus raised from the death at Traus town
\p
\v 7 On Sunday we came together to eat bread . Fol spoke to the people and kept on speaking until midnight, because he was making to go the next day. \v 8 There was many lights in the house where we gathered. \v 9 There a young man name Yutikus sitting on the window. As Fol continued talking for a long time, Yutikus was feeling sleepy. Finally he felt a sleep on the third floors and from there fell down to the ground. When they picked him up, he was dead.
\p
\v 10 Fol went down to the ground, bent over [and] put his hand to him. So Fol said, "Don't worry, he is alive!" \v 11 Then Fol went up again ontop, and ate bread. After Fol continued to talk until daybreak, he left. \v 12 The people took the young man to the house and were very happy because he raised from the death.
\s Fol meets the Efesos head people
\p
\v 13 Fol had said he would meet us at Asos, because he was travelling by walking. So firstly we went on to the boat and travel to Asos town. There we wanted to meet him and to take him on the boat. \v 14 When he met us at Asos, we took him aboard and went on to Mitilan town. \v 15 The next day we left from there and went to Kios town with big boat(ship). The day after we crossed again to Samos, two days later we arrived at Miletus town. \v 16 Fol does not want to stay on the province of Esia, so he decided not to stop Efesos. Because he wanted to go Jerusalem quickly in time for the remembering festival name Fentikost.
\p
\v 17 From Miletus town, Fol sent a talk to Yesu's family(church) head people from Efesos city to come to talk with him. \v 18 When head people arrived, Fol said to them, "You know how I worked among you from first day when we arrived the province of Esia. \v 19 I worked with big low mind( humility) and with tear. I have endured pains because the Ju people made plots to kill me. \v 20 You know that I was without fearing preaching which were helping you but I taught you publicly all through the houses. \v 21 I preached them, to [both] Ju people and Grik people in order that they must turn from sins to God and truly approve(believe) our Lord Yesu.
\p
\v 22 Now in the talk of the God Spirit, I will go to the Jerusalem, I don't know what will happen to me there. \v 23 But I only know this in all cities God Spirit said that in Jerusalem people will put me into the darkness house and will put me in suffering. \v 24 But my bodily life is without.meaning but this is meaningful to me: that I will finish the race which the Lord Yesu gave me, of the work/task of preaching to the good talk about the grace of God.
\p
\v 25 I have gone among you.p, preached the talk of the kingdom of God. But now I know that you will not see me again. \v 26 Therefore now I talk strong talk(declare) to you.p. If some of you die truly without.opprove(without trusting)Yesu, you will not able to blame me for that. \v 27 I was not afraid to proclaim to you whole will of God. \v 28 Keep watch yourselves and all the Yesu's family which God Spirit has appointed you looking.after people(caretakers). Be God's Yesu's family(church) guarding people, [which]he bought them with his own blood. \v 29 I know that, when I leave wild dogs will arrive in among you and will not spare you but strike to kill. \v 30 So some men from your group will arise and lead the approving truth people to follow their false teaching. \v 31 Carefully watch guard yourselves! Remember that for three years I warned each of you without.stop with tears all day and night.
\p
\v 32 Therefore now I commit you.p to God and to the talk of the grace, which talk can stand you up and bless all of you.p whom has set apart for himself. \v 33 I did not desire your clothing or money to me. \v 34 You yourselves know whole that I worked with my hands for my clothes and money and also for my friends. \v 35 In everything I did, I showed work to you.p in order that we should help poor people, we should remember the talk of the Lord Yesu said: '‘The happiness of the man who gives things surpasses the happiness of the man who gets things.’ '
\p
\v 36 When Fol finished talk, they all knelt and talked with God. \v 37 Then they hugged with weeping and kissed Fol. \v 38 They were without joy because which Fol said that later you.p will not see my face again. Then they accompanied him to the big boat(ship).
\c 21
\s Fol went to Jerusalem
\p
\v 1 We said goodbye to them, after this we went aboard the big boat(ship) and were traveling to island of Kos. The next day we went to island of Rodas and from there to Fatara area. \v 2 We found a big boat(ship) crossing to Fonisia area, we went on board and went again. \v 3 After we saw Saifrus area, and passing to the south to Siria area. we landed at Taire area, there people unloaded cargo from big boat(ship). \v 4 We saw the following men there, [and] stayed with them 7 days. By the power of the God Spirit they said to Fol not to go Jerusalem. \v 5 When it was time to leave, we left and went to boat with all the following men and their wives and children from the city. There in the beach we knelt and talked with God. \v 6 After they said goodbye to each other, we went aboard the big boat(ship) and they went back homes.
\p
\v 7 After this we continued to travel from Taire and landed at Tolemais town. There we saw with joy with friends there we stayed for a day. \v 8 The next day we arrived Kaisaria city and stayed at the Filif's house. This Filif was a preacher and one of 7 men who had been chosen to help widows. \v 9 He had 4 single/unmarried daughters who proclaimed God's talk.
\p
\v 10 We had been there many/several days, the God's man who make know(prophet) name Agabus came from Judia. \v 11 He came to us, he took Fol's belt. The he tied up his own hands and feet and said this talk, "The God Spirit said, 'Like this Ju people in Jerusalem will tie the owner of this belt up and will give him the Side people's hands.'"
\p
\v 12 When we heard this talk, we and other people said to Fol not to go Jerusalem. \v 13 Then Fol answered us, "Why are you weeping and making pieces(breaking) my heart? I am ready to be bound and to die in Jerusalem for the name of Lord Yesu." \v 14 How could not we make soft(persuade) him, so we stop and said, "The Lord's will be done."
\p
\v 15 After this, we prepared and went to Jerusalem. \v 16 Some of the following men from Kaisaria followed us and took us to the house of Nason, where we were to stay there. He was a man from Saifros and one of the early/first following men.
\s Fol arrived at Jerusalem
\p
\v 17 When we arrive at Jerusalem, the belivers welcomed us with joy. \v 18 The next day Fol and other people went to Jems, and all the head people were there. \v 19 Fol greeted them and told everything what God had done to the Side people in his work.
\p
\v 20 When they heard this talk, they praised God. Then they said to Fol, "Friend, you.s see how many thousands of Ju people have truly approved(believed), they all follow the law very strongly. \v 21 These Ju people heard what you preached Ju people who live among the Side people. They think that you.p say to them, "You must not obey Moses's law any longer. You must not cut skin of your children. You must not live in the way that Ju people usally live." \v 22 What shall we do? They will hear that you have come. \v 23 So do what we are telling you.s. Here are with us 4 Ju men who truly opprove(believers)who said without.lying talk to God. \v 24 Take these men to the worshipping house, join in their washing ceremony(ceremony of purificaton) and pay for the offering sacrifice. After that they will shave their heads. Then every people will know there is not truth in their reporting talk about you.s, but you.s yourself are living as how law said. \v 25 As for the side approving truth people, we wrote to them our thought that they must not eat food for idols, and blood, and meat without taking out blood, and also sex out of (marriage)."
\p
\v 26 The next day Fol went with the men and they did what was spoken for washing. After they did that, he went to the worshipping house area and told the man who burn the sacrifice(priest), "When the amount of days for becoming without.dust are finished, we will bring sacrifices for that."
\s They held Fol
\p
\v 27 When the 7 days passed almost, some Ju people from the province of Esia saw Fol in the worshipping house area. They get angry and gathered the crowd [and] grapped Fol. \v 28 And they said that, "Men of Israil, help us! This is the man who teaches every people everywhere spoiled our people and our law and this worshipping house. He brought Grik men into the worshipping house and defiles this without.dust(holy) place." \v 29 For the reason they spoke this way was because they had seen outside man Trofimus from Efesos with Fol in the city and they thought that Fol escorted him into the worshipping house.
\p
\v 30 The whole city people ran from all directions. There they caught Fol, they dragged him from the worshipping house. Immediately they closed the worshipping house gate. \v 31 They began to strike Fol when the Roman soldiers big head man heard that the whole city of Jerusalem was in the noise. \v 32 He at once took some soldier's head men and soldiers and ran to the crowd. When the killers/riots saw the soldiers' big head man of soldier and his soliers, they stopped striking Fol.
\p
\v 33 The Soldiers big head man went and held Fol and commanded him to bind with two chains. Then he asked, "Who is he and what he did?" \v 34 Some in the crowd shouted he did this thing and others he did different things. But because they continued shouting so loudly, soldiers' big head man could not pick the truth. So he said to them, "Take this man into the soldier place." \v 35 When Fol came to the steps, the crowd became very angry. So soldiers lift him to protect him. \v 36 The crowd who were following [and] kept shouting, "Kill him, Kill him!"
\s Fol spoke to the crowd
\p
\v 37 When the soldiers were about to take Fol into the soldier's place, he asked the soldiers' big head man(commander), "May I say something to you?"
\p
The soldiers' big man(commander) asked Fol, "Oh, you know Grik language? \v 38 Are you the Ijif man who led arguing recently [and] led 4,000 soldiers into the desert?"
\p
\v 39 Fol answered him, "No, I am not! I am a Ju man, there I was born in Tarsus city, which is famous city in Silisia. Please let me speak to these people."
\p
\v 40 The soldiers' big head man allowed him to talk, Fol stood on the steps and stop/make silent people. When they became quiet, he spoke to them in Ibru language
\c 22\v 1 "Brothers and fathers, listen to my defending talk."
\p
\v 2 When they heard Fol speak to them in Ibru language, they became quiet.
\p
Then Fol said, \v 3 "I am Jew, born in Tarsus city in Silisia region, but grew up in Jerusalem. I learned the law of our fathers and Gamalel is my teacher. I have wanted to obey God carefully as all of you do today. \v 4 I hit to death the people who followed this Way, [and] held men and women and threw them into darkness house. \v 5 The leading burning sacrifice man and all the Ju head men's meeting can testify of this talk is true. They gave me letters to Ju people in Damaskos. So I went there to bring these men as darkness house men(prisoners) to Jerusalem to put punishment.
\p
\v 6 One day about noon, when I was getting close to Damaskos, suddenly strong light from heaven shone around me. \v 7 I fell to the ground and heard a voice and said to me that, 'Sol! Sol! Why are you hitting me?'
\p
\v 8 I asked, "Who are you, Lord?"
\p
He answered me, "I am Yesu from Najaret. You are hitting me,' \v 9 My companions saw the light, but they did not understand his voice who was speaking to me.
\p
\v 10 I asked him, "What shall I do, Lord?"
\p
The Lord said to me , "Get up, go into Damaskos. There a man will tell everything what you do.' \v 11 My groups/companions led me by the hand to Damaskos, because strong light had me blind.
\p
\v 12 A man name Ananias came to see me. He was God worshipper and highly respected by the Ju people who were all living there. \v 13 He stood close me and said, 'Brother Sol, see!' At once I saw [and] found Ananias!
\p
\v 14 Then Ananias said, 'The God of our fathers chose you to know his will and to see straight man and to hear talk from his mouth. \v 15 You will be his watching man to all people of what you have seen and heard. \v 16 Now why are you waiting? Get up, they will baptize you and God will forgive your sins by talking with God in Keriso's name."
\p
\v 17 After this I went back to Jerusalem, I was talking with God in the worshipping house. I saw a eye passover thing \v 18 and the Lord said me, "Quickly go & leave Jerusalem because they will not accept your reporting/testifying talk about me.'
\p
\v 19 I answered him, "Lord, these people know about me that I went from one meeting house to another. I held them to put in the darkness house and beat people who truly approve(believe) you. \v 20 When people killed Stifèn because he said to people about you, I stood there and was one mind with them. I took care of the clothes of those who were killing Stifèn.'
\p
\v 21 Then the Lord said to me, "Go, I will send you far away to the Side people."
\s Fol reported I am a Rom man
\p
\v 22 The crowd were listening carefully to Fol until (when) he spoke about Side people. Then they raised voices with angry and shouted, "Remove this man from this land! He is not fit to live!"
\p
\v 23 They were shouting and shaked his clothes and threw dust into the air. \v 24 The soldiers' big head man sent his men to take Fol to the Soldiers' place(fortress). He told his men to beat Fol. In this way he wanted his men to find out why the crowd shouted at Fol. \v 25 When the soldiers were about to beat Fol, he said to the soldiers' head man, "It is illegal to beat a Roman people whose evil they has not found!"
\p
\v 26 When the soldiers' head man heard this talk, he went to the soldiers' big head man(commander), asked him, "Do not do this to this man. This man is a Roman citizen."
\p
\v 27 The soldiers' big head man(commander) went to Fol and asked him, "Tell me, are you really a Roman citizen?"
\p
Fole answered him, "Yes, I am really."
\p
\v 28 Then the soldiers' big head man(commander) said, "I paid a lot of money for becoming Rom people."
\p
Fol answered him, "But I was born as a Roman citizen."
\p
\v 29 Soldiers who were about to whip and to ask Fol, at once they didn't do it. The soldiers' big head man was afraid, because he told his men to bind Fol, but Fol was a Roman citizen.
\s Fol stood before Ju head men's meeting
\p
\v 30 The next day, the soldiers' big head man were looking for the reason why the Ju rejected Fol. So the next day the soldiers' big head man take the chains off Fol. He also said to/ordered the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and whole Ju head men to gather. He brought Fol and had him stand before Ju head men.
\c 23\v 1 Fol looked straight to Ju head men' meeting and said, "My brothers, I did my work to God until now with good thinking/conscience." \v 2 Then Ananias the leading burning sacrifice man commanded men who were standing close Fol to strike him on the mouth. \v 3 Then Fol said to him, "God will strike you, you look good outside but inside you rotten! You sit to judge me according to Moses's law, but you break the law by ordering them to strike me."
\p
\v 4 Those who were standing near Fol said, "You are insulting God's leading burning sacrifice men!"
\p
\v 5 Fol answered them, "Friends, I didn't know that he was leading burning sacrifice men. Because it is written, 'Don't speak evil to your leading man.'"
\p
\v 6 Fol realized that some men were Saduki men and other people Farasi men, he shouted to the people, "My brothers, I am Farasi man, the son of a Farasi man. I stand on trial because of my hope of the resrrection of the dead.
\p
\v 7 When he said this talk, Farasi men and Saduki men were divided and started to argument. \v 8 Because Saduki men say that dead people will not rise from death to life, they don't truly approve(believe) that there are men carrying heavenly message(angels) and spirits. But Farasi men truly approve(believe) all these things.
\p
\v 9 So there was a lot of noise, some of the teaching men of the law who were Farasi men stood up and started to argue, they said, "We do not see any sin of this man, what if a spirit or man carrying heavenly message has spoken to him?"
\p
\v 10 This argument became so fierce, so fear filled soldiers' big head man because Fol would be torn by men. He sent soldiers to go from them quickly[and bring] Fol to the fortress.
\p
\v 11 That night the Lord stood near to Fol and said, "Don't be afraid! As you have told about me in Jerusalem, you also speak there in Rom about me.
\s They planned to kill Fol
\p
\v 12 The next morning some Ju people gathered and said without.lying talk(agreed), "They would not eat and drink anything until they killed Fol." \v 13 There were many more from(more than) 40 Jews who planned this together. \v 14 They went to the chief burning sacrifice men and said, "We said without.lying talk(promised) that we will not eat until we have killed Fol. \v 15 You and the Ju head men's meeting go to the soldiers' big head man and pretend that you want to find information about Fol. Ask for him and bring him before your court. We will be waiting on the way to kill him."
\p
\v 16 But when Fol's nephew(sitster's son) heard how Ju people had decided to kill him, he went to the soldier's place(fortress) and told Fol.
\p
\v 17 Then Fol called one of the soldiers' head man and said, "Take this young man to soldiers' big head man, because he has some talk to tell him."
\p
\v 18 So he took him to the soldiers' big head man.
\p
The soldiers' head man asked, "Fol, the darkness house man(prisoner), spoke to me. He asked me to bring this young man to you, because he has some talk to tell you."
\p
\v 19 The soldiers' big head man took the young man beside so that people could not to hear and asked, "What do you want to tell me?"
\p
\v 20 He said, "Some Ju people planed to ask you to bring Fol to the Ju head men's meeting place(Sanedrin) tomorrow. They want to see accurate talk about him but they will tell lies." \v 21 [Please] don't do what they ask to do, because more than 40 men are waiting for him to kill. They said without.lying talk(promised) that they will not eat and drink any food until they kill Fol. They are now waiting for your answering talk.
\p
\v 22 The soldiers' big head man said to young man, "Don't tell anyone that you have told this to me." Then he sent the young man away.
\s Soldiers' leader sends Fol to Kaisaria
\p
\v 23 He called two of his soldiers' head men and told them, "Pick 200 soldiers and 70 horse riding men and 200 bow strong people(spearmen) to go Kaisaria at 9 tonight. \v 24 Privide some horses for Fol so that he may be taken safely to Governor Felix."
\p
\v 25 He wrote this letter like that,
\p
\v 26 Klaudius Lisias,
\p
To your honorable name Governor Felix,
\p
Greetings.
\p
\v 27 Ju people hold this man and they were about to kill him, but I came with my troops to rescue him, for I had learned that he was a Roman citizen. \v 28 I wanted to know why they were accusing him, so I brought him to their Sanedrin/head man's Ju head men's meeting. \v 29 I saw that this accusation is in the court about their law, but there was no reason to him that he should die or put him into darkness house(Jail). \v 30 When they let me know their complain to kill him, I immediately sent him to you."
\p
\v 31 The soldiers followed their talk. They took Fol in the night and took him to Antifatris area. \v 32 The next day some soldiers returned to the soldiers place(fortress) in Jerusalem, but horse riding men continued to go with Fol. \v 33 When they arrived in Kaisaria, they gave this letter to the Governor Feliks and handed Fol over to him. \v 34 The Governor read the letter and asked him what province he was from. When he learned that he was from Silisia, \v 35 he said, "I will hear your problem/case when your complaining men/accusers arrive." Then he sent/ordered soldiers to guard in ruling man(king) Erod's house/palace.
\c 24
\s Fol's trial before Feliks
\p
\v 1 Five days later the leading burning sacrifice man Ananias went to Kaisaria with some of the head people and a middle man/lawyer name Tètulus, and they brought their complaints about Fol to the governor. \v 2 When they called Fol in, Tètulus gave his complaint to Feliks. He said, , “You gave us a long period of peace, and your thinking has brought us goodness to our nation. \v 3 Respectful Feliks, for all of this things we thank you very much about this. \v 4 But I don't want to make you tired, I ask you to allow me to say now.
\p
\v 5 We have seen this man is a troublemaker, he made problem to the Ju people all over the world. He is a head man of this group called Najaret men, \v 6 [and] even tried to spoil the worshipping house, so we caught him. \v 7 But the soldiers' big head man Lisias came and took him from us with strong power. \v 8 You can find out the truth of our complaints(accusations) by examining him yourself.”
\p
\v 9 The other Ju people joined in the complaint, he told that everything Tètulus said was true.
\s Fol defended for himself
\p
\v 10 When the governor caused/commanded for him to speak, Fol answered him, “I know this many years you have been a mind spliting(deciding) man over this nation, so I am glad to my defense before you. \v 11 You can quickly discover that I arrived in Jerusalem before 12 days to worship. \v 12 My complaint men never found me arguing with anyone in the worshipping house, and I did not cause to group discussing(riot) people group in the meeting house or anywhere in the city. \v 13 They cannot prove to you clearly these things which they complain me.
\p
\v 14 But one part of what they say is true, which is that I worship the God of our ancesters as a follower of the Way. They say they worship the Ju people's way, but they say I worship in a different truly approving(belief). But I truly approve(believe) everything that is written in the law and what the God's people who make know(prophets) wrote. \v 15 To me is the same hope in God as these men have, there will be rising of [both] the straight men and the evil men. \v 16 So I do always to keep my mind/conscience bright/clear before God and men.
\p
\v 17 After several years away, I came to Jerusalem to bring my people money for the poor and giving sacrifice. \v 18 My complaint men saw me in the worshipping house as I was completing a cleaning. There was no crowd with me, and not any disorder. \v 19 But there are some Ju people from the province of Eisia. If they have complaint to/against me, they should be here in front of you.s and bring complaints. \v 20 Ask these men here, they can tell you that they didn't find me badness(guilty) anything when they took me the court in Ju head men's meeting. \v 21 For one thing I shouted out when I stood in their presence: 'I am on trial before you.p today because my truly approving(believing) is people's rising from the dead!'"
\p
\v 22 Feliks knew well about Yesu's Way, so when he heard the meaning of this talk, stopped the court and said, "When the soldiers' big head man Lisias comes, I will decide your complaint." \v 23 He ordered the soldiers' head man to look after Fol but gave him some rest/freedom and allowed his friends to give his needed things.
\p
\v 24 Many days after Feliks came with this wife Drusila, who was Ju woman. He sent working man to bring Fol. They wanted to listen from Fol about people's big mind(faith) in Keriso Yesu. \v 25 Fol talked about straight life, self-countrol and the judgment day to come, Feliks was afraid and said, "That's enough for now. You may go. When I have time I will ask you to come to me again." \v 26 At the same time he was in thought that Fol would give him some money, so he often met with him and they talked with him.
\p
\v 27 After two years, Forsius Festus replaced/succeeded Feliks's as governor. But because Feliks wanted to do Ju people's desire, he left Fol in darkness house.
\c 25
\s Festus heard Fol's complaint(case)
\p
\v 1 Festus became governor, three days later he went from Kaisaria to Jerusalem. \v 2 In Jerusalem, leading burning sacrifice men and Ju head people arrived before him and made complaints(accusations) about Fol. \v 3 They asked Festus as a favor to them to bring Fol to Jerusalem, for they were preparing a plot to kill him on the way. \v 4 Festus answered them, "Fol is have been taken back a darkness house man(prisoner) in Kaisaria, and I myself will go not.far(soon). \v 5 Let some of your leading men come with me, and if this man has done anything wrong, they can put in complaint(accusation) him."
\p
\v 6 After staying 8 or 10 days with them, Festus went down to Kaisaria. And the next day he called the court and ordered that they brought Fol to him. \v 7 When Fol went inside, the Ju people who had come from Jerusalem stood around him. They brought many strong complaints to him, but they are without.enough to prove their complaints.
\p
\v 8 Then Fol defended himself, "I haven't done any wrong to Ju people's law or against the worshipping house or Rom high ruling man Kaisar."
\p
\v 9 Festus wanted to make Ju people happy, he asked Fol, "Are you willing to go to Jerusalem and stand before me there on these complaints?"
\p
\v 10 Fol answered him, "I now am standing before Rom high ruling man Kaisar's court place, which is straight place to judge me. You.p yourselves well known that I didn't have done any wrong to the Ju people. \v 11 But if I have done something bad, so in the court they would want to kill me, I don't refuse to die. But if they lie in the court then no one should turn me over to these men to kill me. I complain/appeal to Rom high ruling man Kaisar so that he will listen to my court!"
\p
\v 12 Festus talked with his people and then he said to Fol, "You.s have said, 'Kaisar will hear my court.' Therefore, you.s will go to Rom high ruling man Kaisar!"
\s Festus told the ruling man(king) Agrifa about Fol
\p
\v 13 A few days later the ruling man(king) Agrifa and Bernisa arrived at Kaisaria. They.d came to welcome Festus. \v 14 When they.d were spending many days there, Festus discussed with Agrifa about Ju people's complaint to Fol. He said, "There is a darkness house man(prisoner) here whom Feliks left. \v 15 When I went to Jerusalem, the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests) and Ju head people brought complaints and asked me to put Fol pain/punishment.
\p
\v 16 I answered them, “You are saying that this man has done bad things. He must first stand in front of you.p who complained against him. Then he can answer you.p, then I will put him in court who is straight. That is our Rom law.” \v 17 When his complaining men came here, I did not delay the case. But I gathered to the court the other day and ordered this man to be brought in. \v 18 His complaining men got up and spoke. I thought they would say that Fol had done some very bad thing. But they did not say that. \v 19 Instead, they were arguing with Fol about what the Ju people teach about God. They were arguing about who was died Yesu. But Fol was saying that he is still alive. \v 20 I don't know how to examine this complaint. So I asked him, "Would you like to go to Jerusalem and stand for trial on these complaints." \v 21 But Fol answered me, "No, I want Kaisar to listen to my talk." So I said my soldiers, "Guard Fol here until I send him to Kaisar."
\p
\v 22 Then Agrifa said to Festus, "I will listen to him what he is saying."
\p
He answered him, "Tomorrow you will listen to him."
\s Fol apeaks to Agrifa
\p
\v 23 The next day Agrifa and Bernis wore good clothes. They.d entered into Government house with head men of soldiers and respected people from the city. Festus ordered to his people, "Bring Fol here." \v 24 Festus said, "King Agrifa and all who are here with me, you.p see this man! All the Ju people asked me in Jerusalem and here Kaisaria, shouting that he ought not to live. \v 25 But I have not found his bad action which he is put to death. But because he said again he wanted Kaisar to his his complaint(case). So I have made mind(decided) to send him to Rom.
\p
\v 26 I don't know what I should write to the Roman Rom high ruling man(emperor) about him. Therefore I have brought him to all of you. The ruling man(king) Agrifa, I ask you to listen carefully to what Fol says. Then we can talk about the problem together. Later I will write a straight letter to Kaisar. \v 27 I say that because if we send a darkness house man(prisoner) to the Roman high ruling man without reason, then that would not be good."
\c 26\v 1 Then Agrifa said to Fol, "Speak now."
\p
So Fol raised his hand and said his defending talk, \v 2 "King Agrifa, I am glad before you.s today as I make defence against all complaints of all the Ju people, \v 3 because you know well about how Ju people live and their different doing. So you listen to me patiently!
\p
\v 4 "All the Ju people know about me since I was a child. They knew what kind of life I have lived in my own country and in Jerusalem. \v 5 They knew about me for a long time. They will tell that I was a Farasi man. I straightly followed God's law like as all Farasi men are doing. \v 6 My hope is by what God had said to our ancesters, this is the reason I am on trial today. \v 7 He promised a big thing to our 12 Israil families. We all expect to receive what God has promised to us. That is why we Ju people always worship God in the day and in the night. Like these Jews here, I believe in God's promise. But that is the reason that they complained to me. \v 8 God can cause dead people to become alive again. You should believe me when I say this.
\p
\v 9 I wanted to work and to oppose Yesu of Najaret. \v 10 That is what I did in Jerusalem. On the authority of the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests), I put many of God's people into darkness house. When our leading men said, "These truly approving people must die," I became one thought/mind(agreed) [with] them. \v 11 Many time I went around meeting house to punish them. I forced them to wicked talk to God. I was pursuing to angry with them and chased them through foreign people cities.
\p
\v 12 One day I was on the way to Damaskas with the authority and sending of the leading sacrifice burning people(high priests). \v 13 Ruling man(King) Agrifa, about noon, when I was on the road, I saw a light from heaven, not like the light of the sun, but surpassing that, shone and surounded me and traveling people with me. \v 14 We all fell down to the ground, and I heard a voice saying in Ibru language, "Sol, Sol, why are you beat me? When you bump your foot for sharp point of stick, you will feel pain."
\p
\v 15 Then I asked him, "Who are you, Lord?"
\p
The Lord answered me, "I am Yesu, whom you are hitting. \v 16 Get up and stand on your feet. I have appeared to you and chosen you for my works and a witness. You will tell about me what you have seen and will see contiually. \v 17 I will save you.s from the Ju people and the Side people. I am sending you.s to Side people \v 18 to open their eyes and turn them from the darkness to light, and from the power of Sáifèr to God. So they will receive throwing the sin and be given a place among God's people who truly approve(believe) me."
\p
\v 19 So King Agrifa, I was obedient in the eye pass thing(vision) from heaven. \v 20 First I told to whom were in Damaskos, also to them in Jerusalem and all Judia and all the Side people. I preached in order that they must turn from sins to God and do the things that would show by thier turning action. \v 21 For this reason some Ju people held me in the worshipping house courts and tried to kill me. \v 22 But God helped me every day until now. So I stand here and testify the true talk to without.name people and with.name people. I am saying this what the God's people who make know(prophets) and Moses said would happen: \v 23 Keriso would suffer, and be first to rise from the death, would bring the talk of light to his own people and to the Side people.
\p
\v 24 While Fol was still speaking, Festus shouted, "Fol, you are crazy. Your big learning caused you crazy!"
\p
\v 25 But Fol answered him, "Big respectful Festus. I am not crazy. What I am saying is true and with.meaning/reasonable. \v 26 The ruling man(king) knows about these things. I speak without fear to you. I know that the ruling man(king) know what I am saying, because this thing did not happen secretly in a corner. \v 27 King Agrifa, do you truly approve(believe) the God's people who make know(prophets)? I know you do."
\p
\v 28 Then Agrifa said to Fol, "Do you think in a not.long(short time) you can make me quickly a truly approve man(believer)?"
\p
\v 29 Fol answered, "Short or long time, my talking with God for you and all who are listening to me today may become truly approve people(believers) like I am, but I do not want you to become darkness people(prisoners) like me."
\p
\v 30 The ruling man(king), the governor, Bernis and all who was with them stood up. \v 31 After they left and they began saying among themselves, "This man is not doing anything that put do death or putting into darkness house."
\p
\v 32 Agrifa said to Festus, "If this man had not spoken to Kaisar to hear his talk, then we could take him out."
\c 27
\s Fol traveled to Rom with big boat(ship)
\p
\v 1 When it was decided that we would go to Itali, they gave and some other darkness house men(prisoners) to a soldiers' head man (named) Juliès . He belonged to high ruling man's soldiers group(Emperor's Army). \v 2 We went on to a big bout that had come from Adramitum. This ship was prepared [to go]. It would travel to towns on the coast of Esia region. We got on that ship. A man name Aristakus who was from Tesalonika city in Makedinia province, we went with him.
\p
\v 3 The next day we arrived at Sidon. Juliès was kind to Fol and allowed him to see to the friends so that they could give him his wanting things. \v 4 When we left Sidon city, [and] because strong wind were pushing us back, so we sailed through the side of the island of Saifrès where the wind did not blow strongly. \v 5 After this we crossed over the sea to the coast of Silisia and Famfilia area, we arrived at Mira town, in Lisia region. \v 6 In Mira town, there the soldiers' head man found an Aleksadria people's bout which it was preparing go to Italia, so he put us on the bout.
\p
\v 7 We traveled slowly for several days, and had a hard time arriving off Sènidus region. The wind would not let us go that place, so we traveled to the southern of the island of Krit, passing by Cape(point) Salmone. \v 8 We went slowly along the coast and arrived at the place name Safe Harbors, not far from the town of Lasia.
\p
\v 9 By now we had spent a lot of time. so it would be bad(dangerous) if you still traveled by boat because after Ju people's big fasting day sea became very stomy. So Fol said to people in the boat, \v 10 "Friends, listen to me if we go now our big boat(ship) with cargoes will be problem, and we will lost many lives." \v 11 But the soldiers' head man not listen to Fol what he said, but followed the so boat driver(captain) and its owner's talks. \v 12 Because the harbor was not good to spend the raining season(winter) for their staying, many people wanted pass to the harber name Foniks to spend the raining season(winter). Foniks harbor was open to the sea in two ways and strong winds did not blow there.
\s The big wind
\p
\v 13 When a gentle south wind began to blow, they saw good time to go. So they pulled up anchor and went along the coast of Krit. \v 14 But a big wind(storm) name Northeast wind suddenly came them and blew from the island. \v 15 The wind blew strongly against the boat. It was not possible for the bout drivers(sailors) to sail the boat straight into the wind. Then they let boat the wind took it. \v 16 We went along the island of Kauda. The sailors lifted the boat's ndingi out of water for the safety. \v 17 so they lift ndingi up to big bout. After this they started tying around big bout with rope to make strong. Because they were afraid that might be hitting on the stone off the Siritis, they lowered the holding the holing metal of bout(anchor) and let the big boat(ship) be carried by the wind. \v 18 The storm brew so strong, so the next day they began to throw the thing(cargo) from the big boat(ship). \v 19 On the third day they began to throw some big boat(ship) working things. \v 20 For several days we could not see the sun and star. The storm kept blowing strongly and so we came to finish our hope of being saved.
\p
\v 21 In this reason we did not eat any food for a long time. Fol stood and said to the people: "You should have listened to me when you were in island of Krit, you would not see this damage and spoiled/lost things. \v 22 But now I ask you, don't be afraid because no one will be lost, only the big boat(ship) will be destroyed. \v 23 I belong to God, and I worship him. Last night he sent a man carrying heavenly message \v 24 said to me, "Fol, don't be afraid! You will stand trial before the Rom high ruling man(Roman emperor). Because of you.p God will save all who were on the big boat(ship)." \v 25 So don't be afraid! I know that God will do exactly what he said. \v 26 But big bout will bestroyed we will on some island."
\s The big boat(ship) destroyed
\p
\v 27 In 14th night wind drove us around over the Mediterian sea. But midnight the bout working men(sailers) realized we were getting near land. \v 28 They measured depth of water was 40 meter. After this they measured again and found there was 30 meter. \v 29 the bout working men(Sailers) were afraid because we might hit some rocks. Then they let down 4 anchors from the back and they started talking with God for daylight.
\p
\v 30 The sailers wanted to leave the big boat(ship). So they lowered the ndingi into the sea. They tried to go away secretly. They said, ‘We are going to the front of the big bout to put big bout's holding metal(anchors) down into the sea.’ But they cheated. \v 31 But Fol said to the soldiers' head man and the soldiers, "If the boat working men(sailers) don't stay on the big boat(ship), you have no hope for us to be saved. \v 32 Then the soldiers cut the ropes which held the nding and let it fall into the sea.
\p
\v 33 Just before dawn Fol asked them to eat food, and said. He said to them, "For 14 days you have been so worried and you haven't eaten food. \v 34 I ask you, then, eat food, your so you will live. Do this and you will be fine."
\p
\v 35 After talk, Fol took a piece of bread and gave thanks to God. Then in front of every people, he borke the bread and ate it. \v 36 They all peased and ate some food. \v 37 There were 276 people on the big boat(ship). \v 38 When they eat and satisfied, they threw the flawabaik(bag of wheat) into the sea to make (bout)light.
\p
\v 39 In the next morning, they did not recognize the land, but they saw a bay with sandy beach. So they saw mind(decided) to run through the sand. \v 40 They cut the ropes of anchors so left them in the sea. At the same time they untied the ropes which were holding the stears. Next they stand up the saimai(Note. this word means sail from Nemo language) at head/front of the big boat(ship) and the wind started to carry the big boat(ship) to the beach/sand. \v 41 But the big boat(ship) hit a sandbank. The front of the big boat(ship) stuck there and could not move, and strong waves struck the back of the big boat(ship) and everything was destroyed.
\p
\v 42 The soldiers did not want to no one swam to land and ran way so they planed to kill the darkness house men(prisoners). \v 43 But the soldiers' head man wanted to save Fol and he didn't allow doing this things. Instead he said, "Everyone who can swim, jump into the water first. Then swim to the land. \v 44 You other people must follow them. Hold on to pieces of wood, or pieces of the ship.’ So they were reached to the land safely.
\c 28
\s Fol was on the island of Malta
\p
\v 1 When we safely arrived, we learned the island name Malta. \v 2 The island people who were living they accepted well and became friend. They made a fire and accepted us all because it was raining and cold.
\p
\v 3 Fol carried some fire sticks and put them on the fire. The heat of the fire caused a snake to came out and bit him on the hand. \v 4 When the island people saw the snake hanging from his hand, they said among themselves, "This man must be a murderer! He didn't drown in the sea, but god has not allowed him to live." \v 5 But Fol shook a snake off into the fire and there was no problem. \v 6 The people kept thinking that he would swell up from wound or suddenly dying. But after waiting a long time and nothing happened to him, they reached(changed) their mind and said, "He is a god."
\p
\v 7 There was governor Fablis in the island, he owned some of the land around there. Fablis was graciful to us and invited us into his home for three days to stay. \v 8 His father was sick in matress(bed) with fever and stomach troblem. Fol went into talking with God and he placed his hands on him and was became good. \v 9 When this thing happened, the sick people from the island came and became good. \v 10 They were honoring us in many ways, and when we were [time] to go, they gave us [everything] we needed.
\s Fol arrived at Rom
\p
\v 11 Three month after wind destroyed the big boat(ship). The big boat(ship) docked at Malta for wind in the winter. It was Aleksandrian big boat(ship) and there were two gods on the head of the big boat(ship), a we traveled in a big boat(ship). \v 12 We traveled through the sea and arrived Sirakus town and stayed there three days. \v 13 From there we arrived at Regium town. The next day the south wind began to blow up, and two days later we arrived at Fotioli. \v 14 There we found some Yesu's following men, who invited us to spend 7 days with them. And so we came to Rom. \v 15 Some of Yesu's following men in Rom heard about us and came to meet us at the market of Afius and at the village name Three guesthouse. When Fol saw them, he thanked God and received blessing. \v 16 When we arrived at Rom, they allow Fol to live by himself with a soldier was guarding him.
\s Fol preached the good talk at Rom under guard
\p
\v 17 Three days later he called together Ju head men and Fol said to them, "My friends, I have done nothing to hurt our people or the everyday doings(customs) of our ancesters, but they held me in Jerusalem and gave me into the hands of the Rom people. \v 18 They asked me and wanted to take me out, because they could not see/found sins to me which I should die. \v 19 The Ju head men spoke against me, so this thing caused/made me say Kaisar listen to my talk, even though I have no accusation to my people. \v 20 So I have requested you to come here so that I can tell you why I am in darkness house. It is because I truly approve(believe) in Keriso, who is the hope of Israil people has already come."
\p
\v 21 They answered him, "We have not any letters from Judia about you. None of our people who have come from there has reported or said anything bad talk about you. \v 22 But we want to hear your.s talk what you have, because we knew people are saying bad things about this new group widely."
\p
\v 23 They set another day to go to Fol. When that day arrived, many people came together to this place where he was staying. He preached to them from morning to late in the afternoon(evening), explained about the ruling of God, and from the law of Moses and from the God's people who make know(prophets). He told them to repent from sin and to turn to Yesu. \v 24 Some people truly approved(believed) in what he said, but other poeple did not truly approve(believe). \v 25 They argued about it with each other. When they began to leave the house, Fol said, "The God Spirit spoke a true talk through the God's man who make know(prophet) Aisaya to your ancesters:
\q1 \v 26 "Go to this people and say,
\q1 "You will be hearing but never understand.
\q2 You will look but you never recognize.
\q1 \v 27 Because this people's heart has become stubborn,
\q2 they became hard hearing [with their ears],
\q2 and they have closed their eyes.
\q1 So they might not see with their eyes,
\q2 and couldn't hear with their ears,
\q2 and they couldn't truly approve(believe) with their heart and turn so that I would heal them.
\p
\v 28 Therefore I Fol, want you know that God's salvation has been given/offered to the Side people, and they will listen!
\p
\v 30 For two years Fol stayed there his lenting house and accepted them who came to see him. \v 31 He was telling about the ruling of God and taught about the Lord Yesu Keriso without fear and no one stopped him.
